1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:18,118
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:21,855
The best chefs in Korea will
turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:21,921 --> 00:00:24,457
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:24,524 --> 00:00:27,827
<i>-Chef & My Fridge!</i>
<i>-My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:29,963
Welcome, everyone.

6
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,531
-Hey.
-Welcome.

7
00:00:31,598 --> 00:00:37,637
We prepared
a special and meaningful episode today.

8
00:00:37,704 --> 00:00:40,073
-It's called the revenge day.
-A day for revenge?

9
00:00:40,140 --> 00:00:45,478
Our show stars many chefs
who also appeared in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

10
00:00:45,545 --> 00:00:49,249
-Those who lost said…
-On that show?

11
00:00:49,315 --> 00:00:52,619
…"The ones who trampled on me

12
00:00:52,685 --> 00:00:56,523
were seen on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
with a smile on their faces."

13
00:00:56,589 --> 00:00:57,657
How can they stand that?

14
00:00:57,724 --> 00:00:59,759
"It feels uncomfortable to see them

15
00:00:59,826 --> 00:01:02,128
gain popularity like that."

16
00:01:02,195 --> 00:01:05,365
So, if they come and lose again,
they'll admit defeat and leave.

17
00:01:05,432 --> 00:01:07,233
-Today?
-Yes.

18
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:09,602
-Don't they deserve that chance?
-They'll accept the loss.

19
00:01:09,669 --> 00:01:12,238
-Don't you think these two are up first?
-Who?

20
00:01:12,305 --> 00:01:13,706
Ji-sun and Eun-yeong.

21
00:01:13,773 --> 00:01:15,508
-Ji-sun and Eun-yeong. Yes.
-That's true.

22
00:01:15,575 --> 00:01:16,676
<i>Who won back then?</i>

23
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:18,611
Chef Jung Ji-sun.

24
00:01:18,678 --> 00:01:20,280
-Thank you.
-Congratulations.

25
00:01:20,346 --> 00:01:22,315
-Ji-sun won.
-I see.

26
00:01:22,382 --> 00:01:24,684
Actually, when Eun-yeong agreed
to join the show,

27
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:27,554
not only did she want to be here,
but she wanted to fight Ji-sun.

28
00:01:27,620 --> 00:01:30,490
-That was her first demand.
-I see.

29
00:01:30,557 --> 00:01:32,892
I guess Eun-yeong still hasn't given up.

30
00:01:32,959 --> 00:01:34,694
"She still hasn't given up."

31
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:36,663
What's going on, Eun-yeong?

32
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:39,032
I'll only give up
if I lose the game once and for all,

33
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:41,367
so I'll try to beat her.

34
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:43,536
-It'll be fun.
-It will be.

35
00:01:43,603 --> 00:01:45,538
And there are two empty seats.

36
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,874
Among the return match applicants,

37
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:49,776
we picked out two chefs.

38
00:01:49,843 --> 00:01:52,612
-We had to have them here.
-Who could it be?

39
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:55,715
Please welcome
two return match applicants!

40
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:57,117
Please come on out!

41
00:01:57,183 --> 00:01:59,552
The two return match applicants.

42
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:02,255
Which chefs came to join us

43
00:02:02,322 --> 00:02:03,590
for the return match?

44
00:02:04,657 --> 00:02:06,092
For the return match?

45
00:02:06,159 --> 00:02:08,094
APPLICANTS:
BAE GYEONG-JUN & FABRI

46
00:02:08,161 --> 00:02:10,163
Please welcome the two.

47
00:02:10,230 --> 00:02:11,531
<i>Good morning.</i>

48
00:02:11,598 --> 00:02:14,667
<i>A dark horse who trained in one, two,</i>
<i>and three-star Michelin restaurants.</i>

49
00:02:14,734 --> 00:02:16,936
<i>I trained hard at MOSU.</i>
<i>I'm a good chef.</i>

50
00:02:17,003 --> 00:02:18,304
You've improved a lot.

51
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:19,939
Thank you.

52
00:02:20,006 --> 00:02:22,475
<i>I thought I'd win if I fought him</i>
<i>solely with cooking skills.</i>

53
00:02:22,542 --> 00:02:24,277
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

54
00:02:24,344 --> 00:02:26,579
<i>One Two Three, Chef Bae Gyeong-jun!</i>

55
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:28,281
ONE TWO THREE
CHEF BAE GYEONG-JUN

56
00:02:28,348 --> 00:02:32,051
<i>My name is Fabrizio Ferrari,</i>
<i>and I'm a chef.</i>

57
00:02:32,118 --> 00:02:34,954
<i>My restaurant has been given</i>
<i>Michelin stars for 15 consecutive years.</i>

58
00:02:35,021 --> 00:02:36,222
It smells.

59
00:02:36,289 --> 00:02:37,757
AN ACTUAL ITALIAN CHEF

60
00:02:37,824 --> 00:02:39,792
HE HAD A 1-ON-1 MATCH AGAINST
NAPOLI MATFIA, KWON SUNG-JUN

61
00:02:39,859 --> 00:02:41,027
You survived.

62
00:02:41,928 --> 00:02:44,564
A chef who is of Korean descent

63
00:02:44,631 --> 00:02:47,066
won against me with Italian cuisine.

64
00:02:47,133 --> 00:02:48,201
Man!

65
00:02:48,268 --> 00:02:49,836
How embarrassing.

66
00:02:49,903 --> 00:02:51,938
AN ITALIAN MICHELIN-STAR CHEF,
FABRI

67
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:54,007
-Chef Fabri.
-Whoa.

68
00:02:54,073 --> 00:02:58,978
He just singled out Sung-jun
as his return match opponent.

69
00:02:59,045 --> 00:03:00,680
-The skate round, right?
-Yes.

70
00:03:00,747 --> 00:03:04,617
Skate. I can't eat it anymore.

71
00:03:04,684 --> 00:03:08,254
He lost against Sung-jun.

72
00:03:08,321 --> 00:03:12,759
-That guy over there is a fake Italian.
-He's a fake Italian?

73
00:03:12,825 --> 00:03:14,460
He's a knockoff.

74
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:18,298
-I can't lose against him.
-No, you can't. Of course not.

75
00:03:18,364 --> 00:03:21,634
I'm here as a true Italian today,

76
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:24,971
and I came to get revenge
like the Italian Mafia.

77
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,539
Man, he's here to get revenge.

78
00:03:26,606 --> 00:03:28,608
Actually, the fake Italian here is…

79
00:03:28,675 --> 00:03:30,610
-Fake Italian?
-…Chef Fabri.

80
00:03:30,677 --> 00:03:32,579
-Why?
-I have a tip-off.

81
00:03:32,645 --> 00:03:33,646
He's the fake Italian?

82
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:35,882
Every morning when Chef Fabri wakes up,

83
00:03:35,949 --> 00:03:38,885
the first thing he drinks is
iced Americano.

84
00:03:38,952 --> 00:03:40,220
-What?
-Iced Americano?

85
00:03:40,286 --> 00:03:43,223
-How can he drink iced Americano?
-You can't…

86
00:03:43,289 --> 00:03:45,325
-Then he eats kimchi <i>jjigae</i> for lunch.
-That's a secret.

87
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:47,360
-Kimchi <i>jjigae</i>?
-He eats kimchi <i>jjigae </i>for lunch.

88
00:03:47,427 --> 00:03:49,162
For dinner, he eats pork belly with soju.

89
00:03:49,229 --> 00:03:52,298
He was… He was the fake one.

90
00:03:52,365 --> 00:03:53,933
How about Hawaiian pizza?

91
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,835
He might add ketchup to his pasta.

92
00:03:55,902 --> 00:03:57,070
-Oh, no!
-No way!

93
00:03:57,136 --> 00:04:00,506
-Ketchup? No. That's going too far.
-You can't go that far?

94
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:03,276
-This man has changed.
-He has.

95
00:04:03,343 --> 00:04:06,079
Please don't tell other Italians.

96
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:11,251
If they find out,
they're going to denaturalize me.

97
00:04:11,317 --> 00:04:14,153
If Fabri wins the match today,

98
00:04:14,220 --> 00:04:19,392
the <i>Culinary Class Wars</i> ranking changes.
Fabri would outrank Sung-jun.

99
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:20,960
-Let me add one thing.
-Sure.

100
00:04:21,027 --> 00:04:22,462
Do you think I'll lose?

101
00:04:23,630 --> 00:04:25,198
Listen to that guy.

102
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:27,066
What was that? That was cool.

103
00:04:27,133 --> 00:04:28,201
"Do you think I'll lose?"

104
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:29,669
That was really cool.

105
00:04:30,403 --> 00:04:31,671
My gosh.

106
00:04:31,738 --> 00:04:35,541
This next chef also comes with good vibes.

107
00:04:35,608 --> 00:04:37,443
Chef Bae Gyeong-jun

108
00:04:37,510 --> 00:04:40,847
singled out Chef Hyun-suk
for his return match.

109
00:04:40,913 --> 00:04:42,515
I really wanted to see it.

110
00:04:42,582 --> 00:04:47,220
<i>-Their battle was titled the Jang trio.</i>
<i>-I remember.</i>

111
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:50,390
But back then,
Gyeong-jun lost against Hyun-suk.

112
00:04:50,456 --> 00:04:52,625
He'd accept defeat if he lost 2:0.

113
00:04:52,692 --> 00:04:54,327
It's 1:1.

114
00:04:54,394 --> 00:04:56,029
But they were tied,

115
00:04:56,095 --> 00:04:58,264
then, Hyun-suk won
after the judges' contemplation.

116
00:04:58,331 --> 00:05:01,334
-We can't call this a clean win.
-You're right.

117
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:04,137
I often work with <i>jang</i>,

118
00:05:04,203 --> 00:05:06,506
so I thought I'd win easily
when I opened the fridge.

119
00:05:06,572 --> 00:05:09,242
-But in the end, I lost.
-Yes.

120
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:11,778
That means he felt

121
00:05:11,844 --> 00:05:15,214
the judges were a bit harsh on him.

122
00:05:15,281 --> 00:05:17,450
-It's not like he did anything wrong.
-Right.

123
00:05:17,517 --> 00:05:19,419
Did you actually watch the show?

124
00:05:19,485 --> 00:05:22,121
I'm the victim of biased judgment.

125
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:24,557
ONE JUDGE COMES
TO EVERYONE'S MIND…

126
00:05:24,624 --> 00:05:26,359
-Were you the victim?
-That's true.

127
00:05:26,426 --> 00:05:28,261
He didn't particularly like this dish.

128
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:30,663
-He said he just didn't like mine.
-Right.

129
00:05:30,730 --> 00:05:33,933
Come on. I like it. Don't worry.

130
00:05:36,035 --> 00:05:40,106
It's now time to welcome
today's fridge owners.

131
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:43,476
If we may call the chefs star hunters,

132
00:05:43,543 --> 00:05:47,347
we can call these guests laughter hunters.

133
00:05:47,413 --> 00:05:50,183
Please welcome today's fridge owners.

134
00:05:50,249 --> 00:05:51,451
Please come on out.

135
00:05:52,118 --> 00:05:54,153
Today's fridge owners.

136
00:05:55,488 --> 00:05:57,890
Please welcome them.

137
00:05:57,957 --> 00:06:00,760
The laughter hunters! We have a couple,
Choi Yang-rak and Paeng Hyun-sook,

138
00:06:00,827 --> 00:06:03,229
as well as Park Myung-soo!

139
00:06:03,296 --> 00:06:04,497
Please greet everyone.

140
00:06:04,564 --> 00:06:07,233
-Legendary comedians.
-Yes.

141
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:09,135
Please greet the viewers.

142
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,737
Hello. It's great to be here.

143
00:06:11,337 --> 00:06:13,473
EVERYONE IS EXCITED
TO MEET THE LEGENDS

144
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:14,640
Come on in.

145
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:16,509
This place is nice.

146
00:06:16,576 --> 00:06:18,811
-It's nice, right?
-It is.

147
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:20,146
LOOKING AROUND

148
00:06:20,213 --> 00:06:21,447
It's because the show's popular.

149
00:06:21,514 --> 00:06:24,584
-Your studio looks cool.
-Not many studios are like this.

150
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:27,387
Sung-ju, it's been 13 or 14 years
since we last met.

151
00:06:27,453 --> 00:06:28,521
Really?

152
00:06:28,588 --> 00:06:30,123
Back then, you weren't doing so well.

153
00:06:30,189 --> 00:06:32,458
-I'm glad you became a huge success.
-Yes.

154
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:34,961
-Allow us to introduce you first.
-He's right.

155
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:37,029
You've already begun to talk
before we did that.

156
00:06:37,096 --> 00:06:38,564
She's a senior colleague,
yet still clumsy.

157
00:06:38,631 --> 00:06:40,266
I was happy to see him,
so I wanted to say hi.

158
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:43,469
-Jung-hwan, you worked with Yang-rak.
-Yes.

159
00:06:43,536 --> 00:06:47,540
You were really bad back then,
so I'm happy to see you doing well.

160
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:50,376
-Please let us introduce you first.
-They'll introduce us first.

161
00:06:50,443 --> 00:06:52,779
-Please wait.
-You two became big successes.

162
00:06:52,845 --> 00:06:54,680
-She starts off by attacking.
-Yes.

163
00:06:54,747 --> 00:06:58,084
We've invited
a total of three legendary comedians

164
00:06:58,151 --> 00:07:00,686
here on the show today.

165
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:04,357
-Are you two close to Myung-soo?
-Of course.

166
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:05,558
Yes, of course, we are.

167
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:08,127
Comedians all had an edge,
but mine was kind of vague.

168
00:07:08,194 --> 00:07:10,329
Everyone had their own thing,

169
00:07:10,396 --> 00:07:14,100
but I was just a pretty girl
who didn't have a thing.

170
00:07:14,167 --> 00:07:16,202
-It was really hard for me.
-I see.

171
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:19,071
-She just says it like that.
-But then, Myung-soo made me the queen

172
00:07:19,138 --> 00:07:20,673
-with an acrostic poem using penguin.
-Right.

173
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:21,941
<i>-That meme blew up.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

174
00:07:22,008 --> 00:07:23,776
<i>So I got to collaborate with (G)I-DLE.</i>

175
00:07:24,343 --> 00:07:26,312
SHE JOINED (G)I-DLE AND
DID THE "QUEENCARD" CHALLENGE!

176
00:07:26,379 --> 00:07:28,281
Yes, especially with gen Z.

177
00:07:28,347 --> 00:07:31,250
So no matter where I go,
I show people what he said,

178
00:07:31,317 --> 00:07:35,054
and younger people always know who I am.

179
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:38,291
Can you do an acrostic poem
with <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>, with C and F?

180
00:07:38,357 --> 00:07:41,727
-Let us enjoy our glory days too. C and F.
-Do that for us.

181
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:45,565
-I'm sorry, but I quit making poems.
-Just do it this once.

182
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:47,033
-I'm done.
-Why?

183
00:07:47,099 --> 00:07:49,135
I'll only do it on a show
I'm a regular guest of.

184
00:07:49,202 --> 00:07:53,406
I don't want to do it here
and help out someone else's show.

185
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:55,842
He can't think of anything with C and F.

186
00:07:55,908 --> 00:07:58,344
GOT HIM

187
00:07:58,411 --> 00:08:00,346
-You're still thinking about it.
-No.

188
00:08:00,413 --> 00:08:03,049
Well, it's something I can't work with.

189
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:05,084
It's hard to do C and F.

190
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:07,720
I've tried family and friends with F,
but it wasn't funny.

191
00:08:07,787 --> 00:08:09,155
I quit doing it.

192
00:08:09,222 --> 00:08:10,556
Did you just laugh?

193
00:08:12,024 --> 00:08:14,627
-Poong, you're someone now too.
-Why can't you do us some good?

194
00:08:14,694 --> 00:08:15,761
Ask me, then.

195
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:18,331
-C.
-Cold and harsh is the world.

196
00:08:19,065 --> 00:08:21,534
-F.
-Freely ask others for help.

197
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:23,503
Ask for help.

198
00:08:23,569 --> 00:08:24,837
I get the nuance.

199
00:08:24,904 --> 00:08:26,439
ENTHUSIASTIC QUEEN

200
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,241
This world is that cold.

201
00:08:28,307 --> 00:08:30,910
-It's not that funny.
-He can do it on his radio show.

202
00:08:31,577 --> 00:08:32,812
I want to try it too.

203
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:34,514
Yes, sure, Yang-rak. C.

204
00:08:34,580 --> 00:08:38,684
Chefs, when you make
<i>naengmyeon</i>, can you…

205
00:08:38,751 --> 00:08:40,152
Don't you dare let it flop.

206
00:08:40,219 --> 00:08:41,654
-F.
-F.

207
00:08:41,721 --> 00:08:43,089
…factor in some chives?

208
00:08:43,155 --> 00:08:45,124
Come on!

209
00:08:45,691 --> 00:08:47,360
THIS IS SO FUNNY

210
00:08:47,426 --> 00:08:50,129
-It was funny.
-It was.

211
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:52,765
-See? It's not that easy.
-It's not.

212
00:08:52,832 --> 00:08:55,434
-He's the expert and genius.
-You're a genius. How did you do penguin?

213
00:08:55,501 --> 00:08:58,004
-Throw one our way from time to time.
-Sure.

214
00:08:58,070 --> 00:09:01,173
When I look this way,

215
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:03,776
I can see you two
and Chef Hyun-suk in one look.

216
00:09:03,843 --> 00:09:06,846
And the vibe is…

217
00:09:06,913 --> 00:09:08,147
-I can see it.
-They're similar.

218
00:09:08,214 --> 00:09:10,983
-Hyun-suk's mouth is similar to his.
-Hey, you're right.

219
00:09:11,050 --> 00:09:12,652
-Right?
-I can see it.

220
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:15,588
That was why you were funny!

221
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:16,989
Do you get that often?

222
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:19,325
-Since I was young…
-You look like him.

223
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:23,629
…people said I was tall like Yang-rak,
and that I even looked like him.

224
00:09:23,696 --> 00:09:25,264
-Really?
-I see.

225
00:09:25,331 --> 00:09:27,667
Actually, Chef Sam said that too.

226
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:30,736
He told me that I looked like you.
People often said I was a look-alike.

227
00:09:30,803 --> 00:09:32,939
I suddenly remembered something.

228
00:09:33,005 --> 00:09:35,508
-Yang-rak drinks way too much…
-The C and F acrostic poem?

229
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:38,511
…so I was often worried
he'd die an early death.

230
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:40,947
I felt sad
when I thought about what I'd do.

231
00:09:41,013 --> 00:09:42,815
But when he passes away and if I miss him,

232
00:09:42,882 --> 00:09:45,751
I'll go and see him to remember his face.

233
00:09:45,818 --> 00:09:47,620
-What?
-What is this crazy nonsense?

234
00:09:47,687 --> 00:09:49,288
What are you talking about?

235
00:09:49,355 --> 00:09:51,324
We shouldn't talk about
something sad like that,

236
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:53,559
but please grow out your hair
just in case.

237
00:09:54,627 --> 00:09:56,996
-Yes, grow out your hair now.
-Start now.

238
00:09:58,230 --> 00:10:01,500
Our chefs should
brace themselves today.

239
00:10:01,567 --> 00:10:06,339
<i>We often have guests</i>
<i>who are good at cooking,</i>

240
00:10:06,405 --> 00:10:08,708
but Hyun-sook is on another level.

241
00:10:08,774 --> 00:10:11,344
-You're right.
-Not only is she good at cooking,

242
00:10:11,410 --> 00:10:15,381
-but she actually runs restaurants.
-Yes.

243
00:10:15,448 --> 00:10:16,649
She's an expert.

244
00:10:16,716 --> 00:10:19,652
I started when I was 25,
and I'm still doing it now.

245
00:10:20,586 --> 00:10:22,221
-Really?
-I've had ten failed attempts, but now,

246
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:25,324
<i>-I run a </i>sundae gukbap<i> place and a café.</i>
<i>-For how many years?</i>

247
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:27,193
-I've done it for about 20 years.
-About 20 years?

248
00:10:27,259 --> 00:10:30,229
And I've run the café for about 35 years.

249
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:32,064
-My gosh.
-She's amazing.

250
00:10:32,131 --> 00:10:36,035
People line up
to eat at your<i> gukbap place</i> now.

251
00:10:36,102 --> 00:10:37,937
The <i>sundae gukbap</i> place
is doing well.

252
00:10:38,004 --> 00:10:39,605
Lots of people line up to eat there.

253
00:10:39,672 --> 00:10:42,875
She became a certified cook
when she was younger,

254
00:10:42,942 --> 00:10:44,310
but after she turned 40.

255
00:10:44,377 --> 00:10:48,714
<i>She's a licensed cook for Korean,</i>
<i>Japanese, Chinese, and Western cuisine.</i>

256
00:10:48,781 --> 00:10:49,949
You're licensed in all four?

257
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:51,183
It took me a year to get one.

258
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:53,019
You're over 40 years old?

259
00:10:53,085 --> 00:10:54,453
She's 60 now.

260
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,955
-She's 60?
-Yes.

261
00:10:56,022 --> 00:10:57,556
-No way. Really?
-I'm now over 60,

262
00:10:57,623 --> 00:11:00,593
so I came to celebrate that.

263
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,729
-This will be the last TV show of my life.
-What?

264
00:11:03,796 --> 00:11:04,964
Why do you say that?

265
00:11:05,031 --> 00:11:07,299
-What are you talking about?
-I'm now over 60.

266
00:11:07,366 --> 00:11:09,935
Hyun-sook is really serious about cooking,

267
00:11:10,002 --> 00:11:13,673
so she'll appear
in a new JTBC variety show

268
00:11:13,739 --> 00:11:16,976
and show off what she can do.
Can you tell us about it?

269
00:11:17,043 --> 00:11:19,912
It's called <i>Showdown! Paengbong Paengbong</i>.

270
00:11:19,979 --> 00:11:21,180
<i>-Paengbong Paengbong.</i>
<i>-Paengbong Paengbong.</i>

271
00:11:21,247 --> 00:11:22,515
It's titled <i>Paengbong Paengbong</i>

272
00:11:22,581 --> 00:11:25,685
<i>after my name, Paeng,</i>
<i>and Bong of Lee Bong-won.</i>

273
00:11:25,751 --> 00:11:27,520
<i>So it's</i> Paengbong Paengbong.

274
00:11:27,586 --> 00:11:29,255
<i>They went to an island in Thailand.</i>

275
00:11:29,321 --> 00:11:31,991
<i>We really made</i>
<i>what we always make at our restaurants</i>

276
00:11:32,058 --> 00:11:34,460
<i>to see which dish</i>
<i>non-Korean guests would like more.</i>

277
00:11:34,527 --> 00:11:36,228
We sold the dishes
to people around the world.

278
00:11:36,295 --> 00:11:37,730
-It's a showdown.
-A showdown.

279
00:11:37,797 --> 00:11:38,798
Please invite me.

280
00:11:39,932 --> 00:11:40,933
It's already over.

281
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,968
DISAPPOINTED FABRI

282
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:45,705
It'll premiere at 7:10 p.m. on April 19th.

283
00:11:45,771 --> 00:11:49,875
Bong-won and I, Paeng Hyun-sook,

284
00:11:49,942 --> 00:11:52,578
did our best on the show,
even to the point of falling

285
00:11:52,645 --> 00:11:54,046
and tumbling over.

286
00:11:54,113 --> 00:11:56,982
-We worked really hard.
-I see.

287
00:11:57,049 --> 00:12:00,686
Because I truly am

288
00:12:00,753 --> 00:12:02,288
very grateful to JTBC.

289
00:12:02,354 --> 00:12:05,725
I'm already 61 in Korean age,
over the age of 60.

290
00:12:05,791 --> 00:12:09,595
I thought of this opportunity
as my 60th birthday present

291
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:12,198
and did my best
as if my life depended on it.

292
00:12:12,264 --> 00:12:13,466
-It must've been hard.
-I tried hard,

293
00:12:13,532 --> 00:12:17,436
so viewers,
please tune in and watch the show.

294
00:12:17,503 --> 00:12:20,673
Producer Lee Jin-joo, our writers,
and the entire production crew…

295
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:23,576
-I thought this was an awards ceremony.
-Yes.

296
00:12:23,642 --> 00:12:25,511
-I really…
-It's like Baeksang Arts Awards.

297
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:27,646
-Will she retire after this?
-We worked really hard.

298
00:12:27,713 --> 00:12:29,248
Hyun-sook.

299
00:12:29,315 --> 00:12:32,318
-I'm now 60.
-That's enough. He's giving you the look.

300
00:12:32,384 --> 00:12:33,419
I'm sorry.

301
00:12:33,486 --> 00:12:36,355
-We got it.
-I really meant it.

302
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:37,957
-Give her a hand!
-Give her a hand!

303
00:12:38,524 --> 00:12:40,826
AN APPLAUSE THAT SIGNALS
THE END OF THE SPEECH

304
00:12:40,893 --> 00:12:42,628
She choked up here and there.

305
00:12:42,695 --> 00:12:47,366
And now, we'll take a look
at Yang-rak and Hyun-sook's fridge.

306
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:50,503
We have a couple's fridge.

307
00:12:50,569 --> 00:12:52,538
I'm already looking forward to it.

308
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:54,473
-We saw all her licenses.
-I'm nervous.

309
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:57,076
-She probably has lots of food.
-Yes.

310
00:12:57,143 --> 00:12:59,445
She must have lots of ingredients

311
00:12:59,512 --> 00:13:00,613
if she got four licenses.

312
00:13:00,679 --> 00:13:03,449
They are
the first comedian couple in Korea.

313
00:13:03,516 --> 00:13:06,118
Let us present
Yang-rak and Hyun-sook's fridge.

314
00:13:06,185 --> 00:13:08,287
-Here it is.
-My gosh.

315
00:13:08,354 --> 00:13:10,356
-Here it is.
-My gosh.

316
00:13:10,422 --> 00:13:12,591
-Gosh.
-Yes.

317
00:13:12,658 --> 00:13:15,461
PRESENTING YANG-RAK
AND HYUN-SOOK'S FRIDGE

318
00:13:15,961 --> 00:13:17,763
-It's so clean.
-It's neatly organized.

319
00:13:18,397 --> 00:13:19,398
AS EXPECTED

320
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:22,301
-It's very neatly organized.
-There are lots of things.

321
00:13:22,868 --> 00:13:24,470
IT ALREADY LOOKS SPIC-AND-SPAN

322
00:13:24,537 --> 00:13:26,038
It looks so neat.

323
00:13:26,105 --> 00:13:29,175
-It's nicely organized.
-Right.

324
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:30,943
-The side dishes.
-She has lots of side dishes.

325
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:33,312
First of all, I noticed the side dishes.

326
00:13:33,379 --> 00:13:34,914
Those are the side dishes.

327
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:38,884
They're neatly in one, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight, nine containers.

328
00:13:38,951 --> 00:13:42,221
-And back here too. My gosh.
-Five.

329
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:44,356
<i>We usually have many side dishes.</i>

330
00:13:44,423 --> 00:13:47,626
<i>I usually have more than that.</i>
<i>It's usually 30 to 40 kinds.</i>

331
00:13:47,693 --> 00:13:49,195
It's not as much as before.

332
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,130
But you didn't buy these.

333
00:13:51,197 --> 00:13:52,798
-I made everything.
-You made all these?

334
00:13:52,865 --> 00:13:55,067
-She did?
-Let's try it to check their palate.

335
00:13:55,134 --> 00:13:56,936
-What's your best one?
-The seasoned radish

336
00:13:57,002 --> 00:13:59,405
and fermented green chili pickles.
It's made with my family's recipe.

337
00:13:59,471 --> 00:14:02,374
<i>-This must be it.</i>
<i>-Yes, those three.</i>

338
00:14:02,441 --> 00:14:05,644
That side dish recipe was passed down
for 100 years in my family.

339
00:14:05,711 --> 00:14:07,079
-A hundred years?
-Yes.

340
00:14:07,146 --> 00:14:09,348
-You must be a happy man, Yang-rak.
-I am.

341
00:14:09,415 --> 00:14:11,750
That's why he's so healthy.

342
00:14:11,817 --> 00:14:13,018
You never even get sick, right?

343
00:14:13,085 --> 00:14:14,987
No, he never got sick.

344
00:14:15,054 --> 00:14:17,189
-He…
-I did fall sick a few times.

345
00:14:17,256 --> 00:14:19,925
Well, that doesn't count.
Everyone catches a cold.

346
00:14:19,992 --> 00:14:22,561
A cold doesn't count. It's not serious.

347
00:14:22,628 --> 00:14:24,897
He was never even hospitalized.

348
00:14:24,964 --> 00:14:26,232
I've been hospitalized…

349
00:14:26,298 --> 00:14:28,467
But you never complain
about the food, do you?

350
00:14:28,534 --> 00:14:31,237
No, never. I like everything she makes.

351
00:14:31,303 --> 00:14:32,671
I go grocery shopping and cook,

352
00:14:32,738 --> 00:14:35,341
then everything else is his job,
including doing the dishes.

353
00:14:35,407 --> 00:14:36,942
-He throws out the trash too.
-I do.

354
00:14:37,009 --> 00:14:38,477
Can you cook anything?

355
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:39,545
No.

356
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:42,214
She's on another level as a cook.
If she wasn't that good,

357
00:14:42,281 --> 00:14:45,484
-I might try, but I don't stand a chance.
-That's true.

358
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,920
-It happens if the other's a good cook.
-That's right.

359
00:14:47,987 --> 00:14:49,521
-She's that talented.
-It's not easy to begin.

360
00:14:49,588 --> 00:14:52,691
-Wait.
-Let's go down here.

361
00:14:52,758 --> 00:14:55,527
I'm seeing some vegetables.

362
00:14:56,128 --> 00:14:59,298
-She has lots of vegetables.
-It's completely full.

363
00:14:59,365 --> 00:15:02,835
-Cucumbers, <i>chamnamul</i>…
-<i>Chamnamul</i>.

364
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:04,403
<i>-Lettuce.</i>
<i>-Lettuce.</i>

365
00:15:04,470 --> 00:15:07,439
<i>You keep a lot of vegetables.</i>
<i>And bean sprouts here.</i>

366
00:15:07,506 --> 00:15:09,909
-Do you like vegetables?
-Yes.

367
00:15:09,975 --> 00:15:12,544
I prefer meat, but she likes veggies.

368
00:15:12,611 --> 00:15:14,713
-I like Vietnamese spring rolls.
-Vietnamese spring rolls.

369
00:15:15,547 --> 00:15:17,616
-These must be the ingredients.
-Yes, for the rolls.

370
00:15:17,683 --> 00:15:19,618
-These are the fillings, right?
-Yes.

371
00:15:19,685 --> 00:15:21,687
-Do you always keep this in hand?
-Yes.

372
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:23,122
She's always on top of things.

373
00:15:23,188 --> 00:15:25,724
I found this over here.

374
00:15:25,791 --> 00:15:27,559
-There's rice paper.
-Yes.

375
00:15:27,626 --> 00:15:29,528
It's kind of weird for me to say it,

376
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:32,564
but I make the best sauce in the world
for Vietnamese spring rolls.

377
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:34,199
-Whoa.
-I experimented with it.

378
00:15:34,266 --> 00:15:36,902
-Even though you aren't Vietnamese?
-Yes.

379
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:39,271
Let's check out the freezer.

380
00:15:39,338 --> 00:15:42,041
Look at all the meat here. I found beef.

381
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:45,110
-That's sirloin.
-You have a huge portion.

382
00:15:45,177 --> 00:15:46,345
-My gosh.
-Gosh.

383
00:15:46,412 --> 00:15:48,013
-She keeps that at home?
-And chuck flap tail.

384
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,548
<i>Beef brisket.</i>

385
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:51,417
<i>-She's a rich woman.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

386
00:15:51,483 --> 00:15:53,218
I've never seen anyone
who keeps chuck flap tail at home.

387
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,054
-Yes.
-My gosh.

388
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,822
I like beef

389
00:15:56,889 --> 00:16:00,359
because Yang-rak was penniless
when we'd just gotten married.

390
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:01,427
So…

391
00:16:01,493 --> 00:16:02,828
It wasn't that we were poor.

392
00:16:02,895 --> 00:16:05,130
-She even enjoyed pork, then one day…
-He never said…

393
00:16:05,197 --> 00:16:06,498
…she said,

394
00:16:06,565 --> 00:16:10,602
"You weren't well-off, so I ate pork
even though I didn't like it."

395
00:16:10,669 --> 00:16:12,204
No, I do like pork.

396
00:16:12,271 --> 00:16:13,539
But she enjoyed it to that day.

397
00:16:14,206 --> 00:16:16,175
Thanks for making your husband look good.

398
00:16:16,875 --> 00:16:19,712
-Why did you say that now?
-Well, it's…

399
00:16:19,778 --> 00:16:21,647
-It's not…
-It's so unfair to me.

400
00:16:21,714 --> 00:16:25,117
No, I do like pork.
That's why I run a pork <i>gukbap </i>place.

401
00:16:25,184 --> 00:16:28,454
But I do like Hanwoo beef too,
although it's expensive.

402
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,955
Is there a cut you prefer?

403
00:16:30,022 --> 00:16:32,257
-I like sirloin.
-She likes sirloin.

404
00:16:32,324 --> 00:16:33,926
-Sirloin is the most delicious.
-I found it.

405
00:16:33,993 --> 00:16:35,594
-This is pork.
-It's pork.

406
00:16:35,661 --> 00:16:38,464
-It's pork neck.
-It's Yang-rak's favorite, pork neck.

407
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:40,566
<i>-And pork belly.</i>
<i>-Pork belly.</i>

408
00:16:40,632 --> 00:16:42,735
-I like pork.
-More than beef?

409
00:16:42,801 --> 00:16:47,406
-He says it tastes bland.
-Beef just tastes fine. It's good.

410
00:16:47,473 --> 00:16:50,642
-He says pork tastes better.
-But pork tastes passionate and intense.

411
00:16:50,709 --> 00:16:52,144
-So you prefer pork?
-It's pork for you.

412
00:16:52,211 --> 00:16:56,115
Hyun-sook likes beef,
but Yang-rak likes pork.

413
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:58,384
-Don't get the two confused.
-I won't.

414
00:16:58,450 --> 00:17:00,886
-Here are sauces and condiments.
-There are lots.

415
00:17:00,953 --> 00:17:02,621
-Those are mine.
-These two?

416
00:17:02,688 --> 00:17:05,257
This area? I see a can of <i>beondegi</i>.

417
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:07,393
These are great with drinks.
Pacific saury and <i>beondegi</i>.

418
00:17:07,459 --> 00:17:09,695
-I rarely eat anything with a drink.
-Stop lying.

419
00:17:09,762 --> 00:17:11,530
It's as if there's an ancestral ritual
in his tummy.

420
00:17:11,597 --> 00:17:14,767
-Apples, tangerines, peanuts, squid…
-A ritual in his tummy?

421
00:17:14,833 --> 00:17:17,269
-He has a ritual when he drinks.
-Reds to the east, whites to the west.

422
00:17:17,336 --> 00:17:18,971
He needs
everything that's served for rituals.

423
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,173
Have some cola, Yang-rak.

424
00:17:22,141 --> 00:17:23,142
Have some cola.

425
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:26,178
-Come on. Have some cola.
-I'm not dead yet, you punk!

426
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:30,549
Does she make soup for you
to relieve your hangovers the next day?

427
00:17:30,616 --> 00:17:33,318
-Bean sprouts.
-Yes, until this day,

428
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,854
the soup I've had the most often is
bean sprout soup.

429
00:17:35,921 --> 00:17:37,256
-Bean sprout soup.
-Dried pollack soup.

430
00:17:37,322 --> 00:17:39,024
I probably had thousands of bowls.

431
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:40,125
Tens of thousands.

432
00:17:40,192 --> 00:17:42,161
-The bean sprouts.
-She keeps bean sprouts here.

433
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:44,163
-And dried pollack pieces.
-Yes.

434
00:17:44,229 --> 00:17:46,999
<i>Bean sprout soup must be</i>
<i>the food she's made the most.</i>

435
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:51,236
-I'm sick of your drinking.
-That was the couple's fridge!

436
00:17:52,771 --> 00:17:54,373
There were lots of ingredients.

437
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:55,774
And now,

438
00:17:55,841 --> 00:17:57,576
we'll find their order

439
00:17:57,643 --> 00:18:00,979
and contenders for each order.

440
00:18:01,046 --> 00:18:04,450
What kind of food does this couple want?

441
00:18:04,516 --> 00:18:07,820
Here's the first order. Show us!

442
00:18:07,886 --> 00:18:09,655
It's the order.

443
00:18:09,721 --> 00:18:13,559
"It's okay if it's pork-a-licious."

444
00:18:13,625 --> 00:18:15,928
-Pork?
-Yes, a pork dish.

445
00:18:15,994 --> 00:18:18,297
That was his catch phrase. "It's okay."

446
00:18:18,363 --> 00:18:21,934
-It's okay if it's pork-a-licious.
-It's okay.

447
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:23,936
-That's a great quote.
-Yes.

448
00:18:24,002 --> 00:18:25,971
What kind of dishes would you like?

449
00:18:26,038 --> 00:18:29,074
I mentioned that I liked pork.

450
00:18:29,141 --> 00:18:32,678
I don't care what it is, but I want
something that goes well with a drink.

451
00:18:32,744 --> 00:18:34,146
-Like a bar snack.
-Bar snack.

452
00:18:34,213 --> 00:18:35,681
-Bar snack.
-Bar snack made with pork.

453
00:18:35,747 --> 00:18:37,082
A pork dish that goes well with a drink.

454
00:18:37,149 --> 00:18:40,385
Let's find out the next order. What is it?

455
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:42,521
Beef over pork.

456
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:43,856
She prefers beef over pork.

457
00:18:43,922 --> 00:18:44,923
Beef.

458
00:18:44,990 --> 00:18:47,192
-Can you tell us, Hyun-sook?
-Sure.

459
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,061
I'm different from Yang-rak.

460
00:18:49,128 --> 00:18:50,696
-Beef?
-Beef.

461
00:18:50,762 --> 00:18:52,598
-But <i>don</i> means money.
-<i>Don</i> is another way to say pork.

462
00:18:52,664 --> 00:18:53,899
Oh, that <i>don</i>.

463
00:18:53,966 --> 00:18:56,869
-Mr. Italy.
-Mr. Italy?

464
00:18:56,935 --> 00:18:59,838
Can you hear me out for a second?

465
00:19:00,606 --> 00:19:05,144
I really wanted to go to a restaurant
and eat something I can cut up like this.

466
00:19:05,210 --> 00:19:09,314
But he only took me to cart bars
and <i>gukbap </i>restaurants.

467
00:19:09,381 --> 00:19:11,950
-Why was that?
-He didn't have much money.

468
00:19:12,017 --> 00:19:13,552
That's why

469
00:19:13,619 --> 00:19:16,321
I want to eat steak with special sauce,

470
00:19:16,388 --> 00:19:18,991
something I can cut up and eat.

471
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:20,626
All right.

472
00:19:20,692 --> 00:19:24,229
Today is the return match special.

473
00:19:25,030 --> 00:19:26,465
<i>Park Eun-yeong will fight Jung Ji-sun,</i>

474
00:19:26,532 --> 00:19:28,934
<i>and Bae Gyeong-jun</i>
<i>will fight Choi Hyun-suk.</i>

475
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:32,471
<i>This is the first round with ingredients</i>

476
00:19:32,538 --> 00:19:34,606
<i>found in Yang-rak and Hyun-sook's fridge.</i>

477
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:37,809
It's the first match
of the return match special.

478
00:19:37,876 --> 00:19:40,712
The Black Spoon, Chef Park Eun-yeong,
aka the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine

479
00:19:40,779 --> 00:19:45,584
versus the White Spoon, Chef Jung Ji-sun,
aka the Queen of Dim Sum.

480
00:19:45,651 --> 00:19:48,253
-No one can back down from this fight.
-No.

481
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:52,591
When the two had the one-on-one battle
on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,

482
00:19:52,658 --> 00:19:56,061
-Chef Ji-sun flipped the tray.
-She did.

483
00:19:56,128 --> 00:19:57,429
-It was a huge moment.
-Yes.

484
00:19:57,496 --> 00:20:00,399
That's when Chef Eun-yeong
flipped out on the inside.

485
00:20:02,334 --> 00:20:03,835
She was devastated.

486
00:20:03,902 --> 00:20:07,506
That's when she was traumatized
with <i>basi </i>sweet potatoes.

487
00:20:07,573 --> 00:20:09,541
But she joined us on this show

488
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:14,012
<i>and made a dish called</i>
<i>Happy</i> Basi-<i>day and won.</i>

489
00:20:14,079 --> 00:20:17,149
I watched it too.
But she didn't know anything about <i>basi</i>.

490
00:20:17,950 --> 00:20:20,619
-She doesn't know what <i>basi</i> is!
-Man.

491
00:20:20,686 --> 00:20:23,388
She can't just make
a lump of sugar and call it that.

492
00:20:23,455 --> 00:20:25,591
TREMBLING

493
00:20:25,657 --> 00:20:27,326
-The ladies are scary.
-They are.

494
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:30,128
-It's always scary to see ladies fight.
-Yes.

495
00:20:30,195 --> 00:20:32,931
-Even though she's smiling.
-Yes, it's scary.

496
00:20:32,998 --> 00:20:36,134
Chef Eun-yeong was the Black Spoon
in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,

497
00:20:36,201 --> 00:20:38,770
but in <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
you won all three rounds.

498
00:20:38,837 --> 00:20:40,539
WIN RATE: 100%
SHE'S ON A ROLL WITH 3 WINS

499
00:20:40,606 --> 00:20:41,740
Her win rate is 100%.

500
00:20:41,807 --> 00:20:43,675
If she wins today, she'll get her revenge

501
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:45,711
-and take four consecutive wins.
-Yes.

502
00:20:45,777 --> 00:20:47,346
-How do you feel?
-That's amazing.

503
00:20:47,412 --> 00:20:49,281
I don't think I can lose today.

504
00:20:49,815 --> 00:20:52,517
-She became a show-off too.
-She's showing off.

505
00:20:52,584 --> 00:20:54,186
I've heard this from someone.

506
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:55,887
Do I have a follower now?

507
00:20:55,954 --> 00:20:57,923
I became a chef
eight years before Eun-yeong did.

508
00:20:58,423 --> 00:20:59,891
She doesn't sound too humble.

509
00:21:01,193 --> 00:21:02,828
So she needs a good lesson.

510
00:21:02,894 --> 00:21:05,364
-She's setting the tone.
-They're too scary.

511
00:21:05,430 --> 00:21:07,065
She's coming out strong.

512
00:21:07,132 --> 00:21:10,936
Who's more senior doesn't matter
when it comes to cooking.

513
00:21:11,003 --> 00:21:13,705
You're all just business owners
when you're in front of fire.

514
00:21:13,772 --> 00:21:15,907
-Yes.
-You're right.

515
00:21:15,974 --> 00:21:18,043
-Everyone pays their own rent.
-Exactly.

516
00:21:18,110 --> 00:21:20,445
-What's important is the sales.
-Yes, it's the sales.

517
00:21:20,512 --> 00:21:21,647
It's all about the sales.

518
00:21:22,581 --> 00:21:24,750
CHEF EUN-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS: RICE PAPER,
FERMENTED GREEN CHILI PICKLES, SHIITAKE

519
00:21:24,816 --> 00:21:26,985
FLAVORED SOY SAUCE, CABBAGE, CILANTRO,
THIN NOODLES, OYSTER SAUCE, PORK BELLY

520
00:21:27,052 --> 00:21:30,088
I prepared a dish called Dim Sum Goddess.

521
00:21:31,056 --> 00:21:32,057
-What?
-Dim?

522
00:21:32,124 --> 00:21:33,659
-Dim Sum Goddess?
-Dim Sum Goddess?

523
00:21:33,725 --> 00:21:34,893
-She's the…
-Dim Sum Goddess?

524
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:37,596
-I'm the Dim Sum queen.
-Right.

525
00:21:37,663 --> 00:21:41,233
But a goddess is a cut above a queen!

526
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,735
Isn't the queen a cut above?
Is it the goddess?

527
00:21:43,802 --> 00:21:46,271
A goddess is different from a queen.
A goddess is a cut above.

528
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:48,040
A queen is a person,
but a goddess is immortal.

529
00:21:48,106 --> 00:21:50,208
-Is that so?
-A goddess is in another realm.

530
00:21:50,275 --> 00:21:51,810
I'm here before the Queen of Dim Sum,

531
00:21:51,877 --> 00:21:55,881
-so I'll get my revenge by using dim sum.
-I see.

532
00:21:55,947 --> 00:21:57,182
What makes it special?

533
00:21:57,249 --> 00:22:00,085
Dim sums are soft on the inside,
but crunchy on the outside.

534
00:22:00,152 --> 00:22:03,588
But I thought I'd make it soft outside
and crunchy on the inside.

535
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:04,823
It's the opposite.

536
00:22:04,890 --> 00:22:06,792
-Soft outside, crunchy inside?
-Yes.

537
00:22:06,858 --> 00:22:08,627
-Reversed?
-It's usually crunchy outside.

538
00:22:08,694 --> 00:22:10,062
-The reversed kouign-amann?
-Reversed?

539
00:22:10,128 --> 00:22:11,530
-The kouign-amann?
-The kouign-amann?

540
00:22:11,596 --> 00:22:13,899
-The reversed thing is mine.
-Reversed dim sum.

541
00:22:13,965 --> 00:22:16,101
I'll make soft dim sum,

542
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,402
then add a crunchy filling

543
00:22:17,469 --> 00:22:20,272
of Yang-rak's favorite, pork belly,
including all the juiciness.

544
00:22:20,839 --> 00:22:23,308
-What is this?
-I'll make delicious dim sum for you.

545
00:22:23,375 --> 00:22:26,311
-How can it happen?
-Can it be soft outside, crunchy inside?

546
00:22:26,378 --> 00:22:27,646
That's impossible.

547
00:22:27,713 --> 00:22:29,381
-She's just saying that.
-Will she deep-fry it?

548
00:22:29,448 --> 00:22:31,149
She's not just saying that.

549
00:22:31,216 --> 00:22:33,151
-She'll really do it.
-She'll make it?

550
00:22:33,218 --> 00:22:34,286
She won't just say that.

551
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:35,854
THE FRIDGE OWNER
DISTRUSTS(?) THE CHEF

552
00:22:35,921 --> 00:22:36,922
That means she'll lose.

553
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:40,025
CHEF JI-SUN'S INGREDIENTS:
ENOKI, OYSTER SAUCE, PORK NECK

554
00:22:40,092 --> 00:22:42,260
LEAF MUSTARD KIMCHI, SESAME,
CILANTRO, CUCUMBER, BEAN SPROUTS

555
00:22:42,327 --> 00:22:44,930
Up against her is Chef Ji-sun.
What's your dish called?

556
00:22:44,996 --> 00:22:47,332
My dish is called

557
00:22:47,399 --> 00:22:50,802
You Can't Pork Around With Me.

558
00:22:50,869 --> 00:22:52,671
-You Can't Pork Around With Me.
-Pork around.

559
00:22:52,738 --> 00:22:54,840
-You Can't Pork Around With Me.
-Pork around.

560
00:22:54,906 --> 00:22:58,043
You Can't Pork Around With Me.
You have nothing on me!

561
00:22:58,110 --> 00:22:59,811
We're both Chinese chefs,

562
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:03,382
so I'll show her today
that I'm on a different level.

563
00:23:03,448 --> 00:23:04,750
She's on a different level.

564
00:23:04,816 --> 00:23:07,486
I plan to make noodles with pork.

565
00:23:07,552 --> 00:23:09,488
-Noodles with pork?
-Noodles?

566
00:23:09,554 --> 00:23:12,224
People usually use flour,
but I'll make noodles with pork

567
00:23:12,290 --> 00:23:15,260
and season it with sauce,
which will make a perfect bar snack.

568
00:23:15,327 --> 00:23:17,496
I'm sure you'll love it.

569
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,564
-I'm looking forward to it.
-Isn't that magic?

570
00:23:19,631 --> 00:23:21,333
-Right?
-Which cut are you using?

571
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,534
She'll make noodles with pork?

572
00:23:22,601 --> 00:23:24,870
Which cut are you using?

573
00:23:24,936 --> 00:23:27,038
-I'll use pork neck.
-Pork neck.

574
00:23:27,105 --> 00:23:30,375
I'll make the sauce
with leaf mustard kimchi as the base.

575
00:23:30,442 --> 00:23:32,644
-Gosh.
-Noodles with sauce?

576
00:23:32,711 --> 00:23:35,347
I'm so curious.
I've never had anything like it.

577
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,549
I've never had pork neck noodles.

578
00:23:37,616 --> 00:23:40,519
Both chefs, you can do it. You got this.

579
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:43,121
A WARM SUPPORT LIKE A MOTHER'S

580
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:47,426
Let us begin the round titled,
"It's okay if it's pork-a-licious."

581
00:23:47,492 --> 00:23:48,894
I'm nervous.

582
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:51,530
-I love this moment.
-I'm looking forward to this.

583
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:55,600
She'll fight the Queen of Dim Sum
by making dim sum.

584
00:23:55,667 --> 00:23:59,104
The vigorous Goddess of Chinese cuisine,
Park Eun-yeong.

585
00:23:59,171 --> 00:24:01,072
She's here once again

586
00:24:01,139 --> 00:24:04,109
to traumatize her with pork after <i>basi</i>.

587
00:24:04,176 --> 00:24:07,746
The seasoned Queen of Chinese Cuisine,
Jung Ji-sun.

588
00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:09,848
The goddess versus the queen.

589
00:24:09,915 --> 00:24:12,317
Who's going to rise as the winner?

590
00:24:12,384 --> 00:24:16,354
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

591
00:24:16,855 --> 00:24:18,457
The time is ticking!

592
00:24:19,024 --> 00:24:23,328
THE CHINESE CUISINE WOMAN FIGHTER

593
00:24:23,395 --> 00:24:24,830
-We have begun.
-May I go up and watch?

594
00:24:24,896 --> 00:24:25,931
-You may.
-May I really?

595
00:24:25,997 --> 00:24:27,799
If you're curious, feel free to go.

596
00:24:29,601 --> 00:24:31,169
Just don't go into the kitchen.

597
00:24:31,236 --> 00:24:32,804
What's Eun-yeong doing first?

598
00:24:32,871 --> 00:24:34,039
-Rice?
-Rice?

599
00:24:34,873 --> 00:24:37,776
-She's grinding rice.
-She's grinding rice with a blender.

600
00:24:37,843 --> 00:24:39,778
Why are you grinding rice?

601
00:24:39,845 --> 00:24:41,813
I'm grinding rice to make the batter.

602
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:44,115
-I see. With rice.
-She'll use rice powder.

603
00:24:44,182 --> 00:24:47,252
How can she make the batter now?
She only has 15 minutes.

604
00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:49,988
She didn't powder it beforehand?

605
00:24:50,055 --> 00:24:52,624
-It'll take too long, then.
-She's not allowed to do that.

606
00:24:52,691 --> 00:24:56,127
That's how you feel
when you take the cooking license exam.

607
00:24:56,194 --> 00:24:58,697
You have to do it within a set
amount of time and if you don't, you fail.

608
00:24:58,763 --> 00:24:59,898
If you're too dirty, you fail.

609
00:24:59,965 --> 00:25:01,399
-If you peek, you fail.
-When you get licensed?

610
00:25:01,466 --> 00:25:03,502
If the order is wrong, you fail.

611
00:25:03,568 --> 00:25:05,837
So there's a time limit
when you want to get licensed.

612
00:25:05,904 --> 00:25:07,272
Of course. It's the same.

613
00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:10,208
-Chef Ji-sun.
-She begins with bean sprouts.

614
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:12,911
-I love bean sprouts. I do.
-Yes, bean sprouts.

615
00:25:12,978 --> 00:25:15,013
-His hangover food.
-Live with bean sprouts, then.

616
00:25:16,181 --> 00:25:17,749
What's she doing now?

617
00:25:19,417 --> 00:25:20,952
Is that leaf mustard kimchi?

618
00:25:21,019 --> 00:25:22,754
-It's leaf mustard kimchi.
-Leaf mustard kimchi.

619
00:25:22,821 --> 00:25:26,825
-I brought that leaf mustard kimchi.
-That's right.

620
00:25:26,892 --> 00:25:29,194
That kimchi has aged a bit.

621
00:25:29,261 --> 00:25:30,795
2. WASH LEAF MUSTARD
KIMCHI SAUCE AND DICE

622
00:25:32,631 --> 00:25:33,965
THE RICE TURNED INTO POWDER

623
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:37,002
SHE GRABS A SCALE

624
00:25:37,769 --> 00:25:39,004
SHE BEGINS TO MEASURE THE POWDER

625
00:25:39,070 --> 00:25:41,673
-She's measuring.
-She's measuring for accuracy.

626
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:43,375
I thought people with her encyclopedia

627
00:25:43,441 --> 00:25:45,844
wouldn't need to measure.

628
00:25:45,911 --> 00:25:47,445
Couldn't she tell?

629
00:25:47,512 --> 00:25:50,215
-Her encyclopedia?
-Her experience.

630
00:25:50,282 --> 00:25:52,050
-Why don't you get it?
-I'm sorry.

631
00:25:52,117 --> 00:25:53,351
You punk.

632
00:25:54,853 --> 00:25:56,721
-I see.
-Are you just using the powder?

633
00:25:56,788 --> 00:25:58,990
-Yes, just the powder.
-Just the fine powder.

634
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,393
-It'll become dim sum skin.
-The skin.

635
00:26:01,459 --> 00:26:03,562
-Will she mix it with starch?
-She'll mix it with starch.

636
00:26:03,628 --> 00:26:06,064
Dim sum skins can be made with flour

637
00:26:06,131 --> 00:26:08,166
or made transparent by only using starch.

638
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:11,403
But there's really soft skin
called <i>cheung fun</i>.

639
00:26:11,469 --> 00:26:14,639
The soft skin is rolled up
and has to be cooked only briefly,

640
00:26:14,706 --> 00:26:16,708
and it's harder than it looks.

641
00:26:16,775 --> 00:26:20,111
She spent over a minute and a half
in front of the scale.

642
00:26:20,178 --> 00:26:22,213
Chef Eun-yeong,
is it important to measure that?

643
00:26:22,280 --> 00:26:24,649
-Yes, it is important.
-I see.

644
00:26:24,716 --> 00:26:26,818
If it's too wet, it'll fall apart.

645
00:26:26,885 --> 00:26:29,154
If it's too dry, it'll be too stiff.

646
00:26:29,220 --> 00:26:31,423
-It must be important, then.
-It must be.

647
00:26:31,489 --> 00:26:33,725
She spent all her time doing that.

648
00:26:34,526 --> 00:26:36,561
The amount of water is important.

649
00:26:36,628 --> 00:26:38,129
CHEUNG FUN BATTER IS READY

650
00:26:38,697 --> 00:26:40,699
SEARCHING HERE AND THERE

651
00:26:41,232 --> 00:26:43,034
There's not as much fat on the pork.

652
00:26:43,101 --> 00:26:46,137
As we speak,
Chef Ji-sun works on the pork neck.

653
00:26:46,204 --> 00:26:48,473
She's cutting off the fat.

654
00:26:48,540 --> 00:26:51,042
-Why are you cutting it off?
-To use it as lard.

655
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:54,079
-I see. She's using lard.
-She'll use it as the grease.

656
00:26:54,145 --> 00:26:57,082
But Yang-rak said he liked the pork fat.

657
00:26:57,148 --> 00:26:59,985
Yes, I like the fatty part.

658
00:27:00,051 --> 00:27:02,420
It's all included.

659
00:27:02,487 --> 00:27:04,289
It's been three minutes already.

660
00:27:04,356 --> 00:27:07,859
It's been three minutes already.
My gosh, it's so…

661
00:27:07,926 --> 00:27:09,661
It looks really hard.

662
00:27:10,528 --> 00:27:11,630
What will I do?

663
00:27:12,530 --> 00:27:15,133
-She's now cutting the meat.
-Chef Eun-yeong cuts some pork too.

664
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:18,036
-Are you using pork belly?
-Yes, I am.

665
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:19,738
Pork belly and pork neck.

666
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:21,039
-Yes.
-I like both.

667
00:27:21,106 --> 00:27:22,207
He likes both.

668
00:27:22,273 --> 00:27:23,708
PORK BELLY VS. PORK NECK

669
00:27:25,176 --> 00:27:27,612
EUN-YEONG CHOPS GREEN ONION

670
00:27:28,213 --> 00:27:30,148
SHE CHOPS WITHOUT HESITATING

671
00:27:30,215 --> 00:27:31,383
That's so awesome.

672
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:33,985
JI-SUN ALSO JULIENNES CUCUMBER

673
00:27:35,553 --> 00:27:37,122
Look how fast she is.

674
00:27:37,188 --> 00:27:38,390
A VETERAN'S CHOPPING SKILLS

675
00:27:38,456 --> 00:27:41,359
They're both using Chinese kitchen knives.

676
00:27:41,426 --> 00:27:44,062
Chinese kitchen knives.
Those are Chinese kitchen knives.

677
00:27:44,629 --> 00:27:45,797
SHE GETS SHIITAKE READY TOO

678
00:27:45,864 --> 00:27:48,166
I brought those shiitake.

679
00:27:49,267 --> 00:27:51,136
-Shiitake.
-That's our shiitake.

680
00:27:51,202 --> 00:27:53,638
-Those are from your fridge.
-Yes.

681
00:27:53,705 --> 00:27:55,407
I bought those!

682
00:27:55,473 --> 00:27:57,842
-Yes, they're cooking with our food.
-Really?

683
00:27:57,909 --> 00:27:58,910
Yes, it looked familiar.

684
00:27:58,977 --> 00:28:02,647
-Is the mushroom for dim sum filling?
-Yes, it's the filling.

685
00:28:03,214 --> 00:28:05,717
SHE PREPARES THE CABBAGE TOO

686
00:28:05,784 --> 00:28:07,752
I got that cabbage too!

687
00:28:07,819 --> 00:28:08,853
Yes!

688
00:28:09,688 --> 00:28:11,890
It's so cool to see the ingredients I got.

689
00:28:11,956 --> 00:28:13,458
Yes, they're using those to cook.

690
00:28:13,525 --> 00:28:14,592
It's so cool.

691
00:28:14,659 --> 00:28:17,228
It's cool to see them cook
with my ingredients.

692
00:28:18,263 --> 00:28:20,565
That cucumber is

693
00:28:20,632 --> 00:28:22,500
a very delicious kind.

694
00:28:22,567 --> 00:28:25,770
It's really cool to see
the ingredients I got…

695
00:28:25,837 --> 00:28:28,640
-It's so cool.
-It's from your fridge, so yes, of course!

696
00:28:28,707 --> 00:28:29,874
You really do it like that.

697
00:28:29,941 --> 00:28:32,043
-Be quiet!
-How many times do I have to repeat it?

698
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:35,380
Please be quiet! What is this mess?

699
00:28:35,447 --> 00:28:36,548
-It's hilarious.
-"I got it."

700
00:28:36,614 --> 00:28:38,616
They're asking you to stop.

701
00:28:38,683 --> 00:28:40,852
My goodness.

702
00:28:41,419 --> 00:28:43,021
