946
00:38:23,334 --> 00:38:25,903
They didn't make much.
I can't even try it.

947
00:38:26,737 --> 00:38:28,406
What is this?

948
00:38:28,472 --> 00:38:30,908
You should make a lot
and let everyone try some.

949
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:33,110
Goodness, great work.

950
00:38:33,177 --> 00:38:34,745
It must've been hectic.

951
00:38:34,812 --> 00:38:36,514
I'm jealous.

952
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:39,750
The chefs finished making the dishes

953
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:44,522
for Yang-rak and Hyun-sook's order,
"It's okay if it's pork-a-licious."

954
00:38:44,588 --> 00:38:46,624
What was it like to watch the round?

955
00:38:46,691 --> 00:38:48,492
First of all, it's quite moving.

956
00:38:48,559 --> 00:38:52,129
I always had one woman cook for me
in my life, which was delicious,

957
00:38:52,196 --> 00:38:53,564
-of course.
-Remarry, then.

958
00:38:53,631 --> 00:38:54,632
That's not what I mean.

959
00:38:54,699 --> 00:38:57,101
Will you stop taking it like that?

960
00:38:57,168 --> 00:38:58,669
They're so spicy.

961
00:38:58,736 --> 00:39:02,707
But these two great chefs
made this just for me.

962
00:39:02,773 --> 00:39:04,975
It was so moving. Thank you.

963
00:39:05,609 --> 00:39:08,846
BEAN SPROUTS, CILANTRO, CUCUMBER
AND LEAF MUSTARD KIMCHI SAUCE

964
00:39:09,980 --> 00:39:13,217
FLATTENED AND SOFTENED
PORK NECK NOODLES

965
00:39:14,218 --> 00:39:17,655
CHEF JUNG JI-SUN'S
YOU CAN'T PORK AROUND WITH ME

966
00:39:17,722 --> 00:39:19,590
Chef Ji-sun made noodles with sauce…

967
00:39:19,657 --> 00:39:22,293
-In that short while!
-…by using pork neck.

968
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,828
Yes. My gosh.

969
00:39:23,894 --> 00:39:25,429
-You don't eat it separately.
-Cilantro.

970
00:39:25,496 --> 00:39:29,300
-How do I eat it? Mix it altogether? Okay.
-Mix it altogether.

971
00:39:29,367 --> 00:39:32,570
-I wanted to see it, then mix it.
-I'm sorry.

972
00:39:32,636 --> 00:39:35,373
I waited 15 minutes for you. Come on.

973
00:39:35,439 --> 00:39:37,942
-Don't get mad that I took five seconds.
-I'm sorry.

974
00:39:39,210 --> 00:39:41,045
SWEATING

975
00:39:41,112 --> 00:39:42,580
These look like noodles.

976
00:39:42,646 --> 00:39:45,282
It's our first time
eating pork neck like this.

977
00:39:45,349 --> 00:39:47,184
You've only grilled it to this day.

978
00:39:47,251 --> 00:39:48,586
She used bean sprouts too.

979
00:39:48,652 --> 00:39:50,020
It's good for hangovers.

980
00:39:50,087 --> 00:39:52,656
And cilantro. I like everything in here,
including the cucumber.

981
00:39:52,723 --> 00:39:54,392
-Cilantro too.
-It's a good bar snack.

982
00:39:55,025 --> 00:39:57,128
I hope the pork neck
feels like noodles.

983
00:39:57,194 --> 00:39:58,863
-Yes.
-Slurp it in.

984
00:39:58,929 --> 00:40:00,331
You Can't Pork Around With Me.

985
00:40:00,398 --> 00:40:02,333
Those are noodles, so slurp it.

986
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:04,835
Don't just put it in. Slurp it like this.

987
00:40:04,902 --> 00:40:06,270
Be quiet!

988
00:40:07,438 --> 00:40:10,040
-Stay quiet!
-Chef Ji-sun's dish.

989
00:40:10,107 --> 00:40:11,108
Yes.

990
00:40:11,175 --> 00:40:13,744
She used pork neck

991
00:40:13,811 --> 00:40:15,546
-to make noodles.
-Yes.

992
00:40:15,613 --> 00:40:17,548
-Does it feel like noodles?
-Slurp it.

993
00:40:17,615 --> 00:40:18,816
Tell us.

994
00:40:19,917 --> 00:40:22,353
SAVORING

995
00:40:23,454 --> 00:40:26,824
-He eats pork neck and veggies.
-Is it seasoned well?

996
00:40:27,525 --> 00:40:28,759
-My gosh.
-"My gosh."

997
00:40:28,826 --> 00:40:30,494
Why? Say something.

998
00:40:30,561 --> 00:40:32,630
I've only had grilled pork neck.

999
00:40:32,696 --> 00:40:35,065
But this dish contained

1000
00:40:35,132 --> 00:40:38,602
about 70% of the pork neck flavor,

1001
00:40:38,669 --> 00:40:42,139
<i>and it's mixed with a perfect amount</i>
<i>of cilantro and bean sprouts.</i>

1002
00:40:42,206 --> 00:40:45,142
I want to give this 120 points.

1003
00:40:45,209 --> 00:40:46,377
The pork neck.

1004
00:40:46,444 --> 00:40:48,145
Do you usually just grill the pork?

1005
00:40:48,212 --> 00:40:49,647
-Yes.
-I only grill it.

1006
00:40:49,713 --> 00:40:50,981
That's all I do.

1007
00:40:51,048 --> 00:40:54,552
I thought it was illegal
to eat it in another way.

1008
00:40:54,618 --> 00:40:56,454
This is such a new way.

1009
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:57,588
It's a noodle dish.

1010
00:40:57,655 --> 00:41:00,124
-How's the sauce?
-It's like bulgogi.

1011
00:41:00,191 --> 00:41:02,526
It's not too strong.

1012
00:41:02,593 --> 00:41:04,962
It's just subtle.

1013
00:41:05,029 --> 00:41:06,030
She took a good bite.

1014
00:41:06,096 --> 00:41:08,499
Hyun-sook is not an easy judge to please.

1015
00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:10,334
-My gosh.
-She's honest about her feelings.

1016
00:41:10,401 --> 00:41:15,139
She coated the pork neck
with some starch,

1017
00:41:15,206 --> 00:41:17,575
then boiled it in hot water.

1018
00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:20,110
-It's chewy.
-I'm curious to death.

1019
00:41:20,177 --> 00:41:22,847
Yet the texture is amazingly soft.

1020
00:41:22,913 --> 00:41:25,950
On top of that,
the smell of cilantro hits me at the end,

1021
00:41:26,016 --> 00:41:27,818
mixed with the crunchy bean sprouts.

1022
00:41:27,885 --> 00:41:29,887
This isn't TV shopping.

1023
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:32,323
You can't share that with us
like it's TV shopping.

1024
00:41:32,389 --> 00:41:34,458
You aren't here to sell that.

1025
00:41:34,525 --> 00:41:35,793
Tell me about the sauce.

1026
00:41:35,860 --> 00:41:39,129
You can just share your opinions.

1027
00:41:39,763 --> 00:41:42,399
She used leaf mustard kimchi
to make the sauce.

1028
00:41:42,466 --> 00:41:47,738
And this kimchi leaves behind that
bitter yet aromatic leaf mustard smell.

1029
00:41:47,805 --> 00:41:50,441
It tastes deep, chewy,

1030
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:53,043
soft, yet crunchy.

1031
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:54,945
It's really delicious.

1032
00:41:55,012 --> 00:41:58,082
You'll regret it forever
if you don't try this.

1033
00:41:58,148 --> 00:41:59,917
It's almost sold out!

1034
00:41:59,984 --> 00:42:01,418
Yes, it's almost sold out.

1035
00:42:01,485 --> 00:42:03,988
I almost made the call just now.

1036
00:42:04,054 --> 00:42:06,991
-I'm sorry.
-It's already sold out.

1037
00:42:07,057 --> 00:42:09,660
I've never tasted
anything like this in Korea.

1038
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:11,262
Would it go well with drinks?

1039
00:42:11,328 --> 00:42:12,997
-Yes, it's excellent.
-It is?

1040
00:42:13,063 --> 00:42:14,498
What kind of alcohol?

1041
00:42:14,565 --> 00:42:16,166
<i>Makgeolli</i> would go well with this.

1042
00:42:16,233 --> 00:42:17,601
How about Chinese liquor?
It's a Chinese dish.

1043
00:42:17,668 --> 00:42:20,471
-Yes, kaoliang liquor.
-That's true. Kaoliang liquor.

1044
00:42:20,538 --> 00:42:21,539
You should have that.

1045
00:42:21,605 --> 00:42:23,007
It'd go well with kaoliang liquor.

1046
00:42:23,073 --> 00:42:25,543
The couple is looking very happy now.

1047
00:42:25,609 --> 00:42:27,177
-Thank you.
-And <i>makgeolli</i>.

1048
00:42:27,244 --> 00:42:30,648
And next,
Chef Eun-yeong's Dim Sum Goddess.

1049
00:42:30,714 --> 00:42:33,117
SOFT OUTSIDE, CRUNCHY INSIDE,
A DIM SUM WITH PORK BELLY FILLING

1050
00:42:34,018 --> 00:42:37,655
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG'S
DIM SUM GODDESS

1051
00:42:37,721 --> 00:42:39,957
Chef Eun-yeong, gosh.

1052
00:42:40,024 --> 00:42:41,191
I remember

1053
00:42:41,258 --> 00:42:43,961
how she ground up rice or something
for a long time.

1054
00:42:45,763 --> 00:42:47,965
You gave me such a big portion.

1055
00:42:48,032 --> 00:42:49,567
Is it too little?

1056
00:42:50,301 --> 00:42:52,303
I can't share it with anyone.

1057
00:42:52,369 --> 00:42:53,837
A huge portion?

1058
00:42:53,904 --> 00:42:56,840
I was running out of time.

1059
00:42:56,907 --> 00:42:59,243
Should he try the sauce separately?

1060
00:42:59,310 --> 00:43:02,046
There's nothing I can eat.
There isn't enough sauce.

1061
00:43:02,112 --> 00:43:03,113
You don't eat the sauce.

1062
00:43:03,180 --> 00:43:06,750
He's a bit disappointed
because of the portion.

1063
00:43:06,817 --> 00:43:08,185
-Just…
-Where's the sauce?

1064
00:43:08,252 --> 00:43:09,820
Just dip it lightly.

1065
00:43:11,088 --> 00:43:12,823
You just need to grab one and eat it.

1066
00:43:12,890 --> 00:43:15,125
-The dim sum absorbed everything.
-It's all evaporated.

1067
00:43:15,192 --> 00:43:18,028
-The dim sum absorbed everything.
-It's in the skin.

1068
00:43:19,463 --> 00:43:20,464
Try the sauce separately.

1069
00:43:21,031 --> 00:43:23,567
GETTING EVIDENCE(?)
TO PROVE THE LACK OF SAUCE

1070
00:43:23,634 --> 00:43:24,635
That's not how you eat it.

1071
00:43:24,702 --> 00:43:26,704
Did you give him sauce or what?

1072
00:43:26,770 --> 00:43:27,871
No, it's all in the skin.

1073
00:43:27,938 --> 00:43:31,442
-It's a bit salty. It's good.
-Yes, it should be.

1074
00:43:31,508 --> 00:43:32,776
It's the portion.

1075
00:43:32,843 --> 00:43:35,479
I'll make a bigger portion next time.

1076
00:43:35,546 --> 00:43:38,248
-It's not a lot.
-Dim Sum Goddess.

1077
00:43:38,315 --> 00:43:39,883
It's an honor.

1078
00:43:39,950 --> 00:43:41,685
-Everything will be decided now.
-Be serious.

1079
00:43:41,752 --> 00:43:43,921
No one else needs to eat it.
I'm supposed to try this.

1080
00:43:43,988 --> 00:43:46,223
-She made it for me.
-It's for the fridge owner.

1081
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:48,525
It'd be a waste if she made too much.

1082
00:43:48,592 --> 00:43:50,961
-You're talking too much.
-Will you just eat it?

1083
00:43:51,028 --> 00:43:53,163
You're so frustrating.

1084
00:43:53,230 --> 00:43:55,265
But it's so precious.
I get just two bites.

1085
00:43:55,332 --> 00:43:57,901
-Just eat it!
-Wait, Yang-rak.

1086
00:43:57,968 --> 00:43:59,970
-Let me take a photo.
-Okay.

1087
00:44:00,037 --> 00:44:02,039
You don't have to take a picture!

1088
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:05,609
Just eat it!

1089
00:44:06,443 --> 00:44:09,580
Just eat it!

1090
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:10,848
Come on!

1091
00:44:11,482 --> 00:44:12,483
HE FINALLY EATS THE DIM SUM

1092
00:44:12,549 --> 00:44:15,686
-He ate it.
-Why is everything so funny today?

1093
00:44:15,753 --> 00:44:19,156
He just had it.
Soft outside, crunchy inside.

1094
00:44:19,223 --> 00:44:21,492
-It's soft on the outside.
-Feel it, Yang-rak.

1095
00:44:21,558 --> 00:44:24,561
-And yes, it's crunchy on the inside.
-It's crunchy.

1096
00:44:24,628 --> 00:44:28,132
-It's savory and delicious, but…
-It's crunchy. But?

1097
00:44:28,198 --> 00:44:30,000
-It's great, but…
-But?

1098
00:44:30,067 --> 00:44:32,603
-One thing is a shame.
-Yes?

1099
00:44:32,670 --> 00:44:36,073
It almost feels like
there's no pork inside.

1100
00:44:36,140 --> 00:44:37,508
-It was a pork round.
-Gosh.

1101
00:44:37,574 --> 00:44:39,343
The texture must've been too strong.

1102
00:44:39,410 --> 00:44:43,113
It's like pork was cast
as the main character,

1103
00:44:43,180 --> 00:44:46,216
but it ended up becoming
the third most important role.

1104
00:44:46,283 --> 00:44:48,619
But I can taste it. It's there.

1105
00:44:48,686 --> 00:44:50,587
You rolled up lots of pork inside.

1106
00:44:50,654 --> 00:44:52,990
I split it into two,
so it might be all on one side.

1107
00:44:53,057 --> 00:44:55,859
I got so unlucky
and chose the wrong piece.

1108
00:44:55,926 --> 00:44:59,129
I didn't pick the right one.
You should try this.

1109
00:44:59,196 --> 00:45:01,598
He got unlucky?

1110
00:45:01,665 --> 00:45:03,934
-The pork.
-That was more important to me.

1111
00:45:04,001 --> 00:45:06,503
-It was supposed to be the main character.
-I couldn't spot it.

1112
00:45:06,570 --> 00:45:09,073
But it was so delicious.

1113
00:45:09,139 --> 00:45:10,641
STOP WHINING AND OPEN UP

1114
00:45:10,708 --> 00:45:12,743
You two are driving me crazy.

1115
00:45:14,344 --> 00:45:17,614
-How is it?
-I can taste the pork here.

1116
00:45:17,681 --> 00:45:19,950
It's about 50%.

1117
00:45:20,017 --> 00:45:22,853
The pork was mostly on this side.

1118
00:45:22,920 --> 00:45:25,189
-You should try it, Hyun-sook.
-It looks good.

1119
00:45:25,255 --> 00:45:28,025
The TV shopping begins.

1120
00:45:28,092 --> 00:45:29,259
How is it, Hyun-sook?

1121
00:45:29,326 --> 00:45:30,394
OH, MY

1122
00:45:30,461 --> 00:45:32,763
This is TV shopping.

1123
00:45:32,830 --> 00:45:35,432
-I want to buy it again.
-How much does she want to sell today?

1124
00:45:35,499 --> 00:45:39,236
The texture of pork and vegetables

1125
00:45:39,303 --> 00:45:41,839
all come together
and began to dance in my mouth.

1126
00:45:43,073 --> 00:45:45,242
They're perfectly compatible.

1127
00:45:45,309 --> 00:45:47,077
Myung-soo will try

1128
00:45:47,144 --> 00:45:49,513
-Wait.
-Chef Ji-sun's dish first.

1129
00:45:49,580 --> 00:45:51,582
-It smells like <i>jjajangmyeon</i>.
-It does?

1130
00:45:51,648 --> 00:45:53,817
-Yes, a bit. Smell it.
-It must be the soy sauce.

1131
00:45:53,884 --> 00:45:56,353
-It smells like <i>jjajangmyeon</i>?
-Yes.

1132
00:45:56,420 --> 00:45:58,589
-Let me try the pork neck.
-It must be the pork too.

1133
00:45:58,655 --> 00:45:59,823
It looks good.

1134
00:46:01,592 --> 00:46:04,528
I wonder what Myung-soo will say.
He looks very serious.

1135
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:05,963
It must be tough to evaluate.

1136
00:46:06,029 --> 00:46:08,766
His eyes are sharp.
They're looking sensitive.

1137
00:46:08,832 --> 00:46:10,934
I hope it feels like noodles.

1138
00:46:11,001 --> 00:46:13,637
Overall, it tastes like

1139
00:46:13,704 --> 00:46:16,974
noodles mixed with spicy sauce.
It tastes great.

1140
00:46:17,040 --> 00:46:19,710
-But the meat didn't feel like noodles.
-The meat?

1141
00:46:19,777 --> 00:46:21,979
-It just tastes like meat.
-Meat was just meat.

1142
00:46:22,045 --> 00:46:23,147
I can't call these noodles.

1143
00:46:23,213 --> 00:46:25,282
-I see.
-These aren't noodles.

1144
00:46:25,349 --> 00:46:26,416
Got it?

1145
00:46:26,984 --> 00:46:29,586
These aren't noodles.
These are pieces of meat!

1146
00:46:29,653 --> 00:46:31,488
But if I eat it like this,

1147
00:46:31,555 --> 00:46:34,458
I won't have to eat vegetables separately.

1148
00:46:34,525 --> 00:46:38,996
Even if you eat it like this,
it still feels like vegetable wrap.

1149
00:46:39,062 --> 00:46:41,932
This time, it's Chef Eun-yeong's dim sum.

1150
00:46:41,999 --> 00:46:44,268
-He smells it first.
-He must be a gourmet.

1151
00:46:44,334 --> 00:46:46,637
-It's soy sauce.
-Yes, it's soy sauce-based.

1152
00:46:46,703 --> 00:46:49,106
-Will he eat everything in one bite?
-One bite?

1153
00:46:49,173 --> 00:46:51,175
Myung-soo took a big bite.

1154
00:46:51,241 --> 00:46:52,242
It looks good.

1155
00:46:52,743 --> 00:46:53,744
A big bite.

1156
00:46:54,545 --> 00:46:55,979
-I'm curious.
-Yes.

1157
00:46:56,046 --> 00:46:57,548
-It's very…
-I can taste lots of pork.

1158
00:46:57,614 --> 00:47:00,017
He can taste the pork.
It must be acting as the main character.

1159
00:47:00,083 --> 00:47:01,752
I think she put in a lot for this one.

1160
00:47:03,220 --> 00:47:04,221
You got her.

1161
00:47:04,288 --> 00:47:07,291
-You got her.
-You got her.

1162
00:47:07,357 --> 00:47:10,294
-Eun-yeong, he got you.
-I did put in some more.

1163
00:47:10,360 --> 00:47:14,565
The texture of the skin
and the crunchiness

1164
00:47:14,631 --> 00:47:16,266
oddly come together and work well.

1165
00:47:16,333 --> 00:47:17,935
-I see.
-Thank you.

1166
00:47:18,001 --> 00:47:19,703
-It's good too. It's not too salty.
-It's not?

1167
00:47:19,770 --> 00:47:21,071
She must've removed some soy sauce.

1168
00:47:22,172 --> 00:47:24,708
-I told her to leave it out.
-I knew it.

1169
00:47:24,775 --> 00:47:27,244
It's really good. It's good.

1170
00:47:27,311 --> 00:47:30,681
But Yang-rak, you'll decide
with the dishes you had.

1171
00:47:30,747 --> 00:47:33,951
He's not asking his wife.
He'll make the call.

1172
00:47:34,017 --> 00:47:35,219
I should.

1173
00:47:35,285 --> 00:47:36,820
Press one for Park Eun-yeong.

1174
00:47:36,887 --> 00:47:38,388
Press two for Jung Ji-sun.

1175
00:47:38,455 --> 00:47:40,123
I'm sorry, the dropout.

1176
00:47:40,190 --> 00:47:43,060
Please don't be hard on me.

1177
00:47:43,126 --> 00:47:44,127
Be hard on him.

1178
00:47:44,194 --> 00:47:46,363
We got the result.

1179
00:47:46,430 --> 00:47:47,931
You're unable to look at the chefs.

1180
00:47:47,998 --> 00:47:52,603
I'm getting sweaty.
I'm bad at these things.

1181
00:47:52,669 --> 00:47:55,372
Show us Yang-rak's decision.

1182
00:47:56,306 --> 00:47:59,042
It's okay if it's pork-a-licious.

1183
00:47:59,109 --> 00:48:02,212
Will Chef Ji-sun win again
and take another victory?

1184
00:48:02,279 --> 00:48:07,351
Or will Chef Eun-yeong get her revenge?

1185
00:48:07,417 --> 00:48:10,554
Which dish did Yang-rak choose?

1186
00:48:11,355 --> 00:48:14,758
Who's the winner of the pork dish round?

1187
00:48:15,425 --> 00:48:16,894
The winner is?

1188
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:18,829
JUNG JI-SUN WINS

1189
00:48:18,896 --> 00:48:20,964
CHEF JUNG JI-SUN'S
YOU CAN'T PORK AROUND WITH ME WINS

1190
00:48:21,031 --> 00:48:22,866
Chef Ji-sun wins.

1191
00:48:23,467 --> 00:48:26,169
-Chef Ji-sun seized the victory again.
-Jeez.

1192
00:48:26,236 --> 00:48:27,838
-I'm so sorry.
-It's okay.

1193
00:48:27,905 --> 00:48:30,741
Ji-sun with more experience wins.

1194
00:48:30,807 --> 00:48:32,276
-Once again, she wins…
-Right.

1195
00:48:32,342 --> 00:48:34,711
…against Chef Eun-yeong
after her victory in <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1196
00:48:34,778 --> 00:48:39,216
-As I mentioned, I like pork.
-There was one reason.

1197
00:48:39,283 --> 00:48:41,218
-It was better as a bar snack.
-And I wanted this…

1198
00:48:41,285 --> 00:48:43,854
-As a bar snack.
-…as a bar snack, yes.

1199
00:48:43,921 --> 00:48:45,856
It felt like you saw right through me.

1200
00:48:45,923 --> 00:48:48,926
-Both dishes were absolutely delicious.
-They were.

1201
00:48:48,992 --> 00:48:50,627
-I feel so bad.
-It's okay.

1202
00:48:50,694 --> 00:48:52,829
Who would you have chosen, Myung-soo?

1203
00:48:52,896 --> 00:48:54,865
Why should I tell you?
It wasn't my decision.

1204
00:48:55,565 --> 00:48:59,136
-I don't want to make a chef my enemy.
-He can't choose one.

1205
00:48:59,202 --> 00:49:01,638
I don't want to make a chef my enemy.
I'll talk when they cook for me.

1206
00:49:01,705 --> 00:49:03,941
That's how he's survived in this field.

1207
00:49:04,007 --> 00:49:06,910
Yang-rak will give her a star.

1208
00:49:06,977 --> 00:49:09,546
Ji-sun takes her second win!

1209
00:49:09,613 --> 00:49:11,481
-Thank you.
-The second win.

1210
00:49:11,548 --> 00:49:13,684
That's Jung Ji-sun for you.

1211
00:49:13,750 --> 00:49:15,385
PROUD

1212
00:49:15,452 --> 00:49:18,789
<i>This is the second return match</i>

1213
00:49:18,855 --> 00:49:22,025
<i>using ingredients</i>
<i>from Yang-rak and Hyun-sook's fridge.</i>

1214
00:49:22,092 --> 00:49:24,962
One Two Three, Chef Bae Gyeong-jun

1215
00:49:25,028 --> 00:49:30,133
versus six-star chef of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

1216
00:49:30,200 --> 00:49:31,735
-Six stars? Whoa.
-Yes.

1217
00:49:31,802 --> 00:49:35,105
Hyun-suk is currently first place
with six stars.

1218
00:49:35,172 --> 00:49:38,041
<i>When they were on</i> Culinary Class Wars,

1219
00:49:38,108 --> 00:49:40,844
-Chef Hyun-suk won.
-Right.

1220
00:49:40,911 --> 00:49:43,013
But it was a close fight.

1221
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:44,982
Some say Hyun-suk got scared.

1222
00:49:45,048 --> 00:49:47,117
-He was scared?
-He must've been.

1223
00:49:47,184 --> 00:49:49,720
They made the judges have a discussion.

1224
00:49:49,786 --> 00:49:51,355
If there was a debate, it means

1225
00:49:51,421 --> 00:49:53,223
Chef Hyun-suk didn't have
an overwhelming victory.

1226
00:49:53,290 --> 00:49:55,359
-Yes.
-It was debatable.

1227
00:49:55,425 --> 00:49:56,426
A hair of difference.

1228
00:49:56,493 --> 00:49:58,061
-It wasn't a definite win.
-That's important.

1229
00:49:58,128 --> 00:50:01,498
I do admit that I won by a hair.

1230
00:50:01,565 --> 00:50:03,233
I don't know if I can say this,

1231
00:50:03,300 --> 00:50:05,035
but if I didn't make it to the next round,

1232
00:50:05,102 --> 00:50:07,004
would <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>
have been as entertaining?

1233
00:50:07,070 --> 00:50:09,272
Yes, it would've been entertaining.

1234
00:50:09,339 --> 00:50:12,376
Wait, were you the entertainer there?

1235
00:50:12,442 --> 00:50:15,645
-He must've been Kim Poong of the show.
-I see.

1236
00:50:17,114 --> 00:50:18,548
You're…

1237
00:50:18,615 --> 00:50:21,551
-No cussing.
-Don't cuss in the kitchen.

1238
00:50:21,618 --> 00:50:22,819
No cussing.

1239
00:50:22,886 --> 00:50:25,422
Poong, I can't reach you,
but I have lots of things I can throw.

1240
00:50:27,324 --> 00:50:28,859
Were you in eighth place?

1241
00:50:28,925 --> 00:50:30,961
-I was in eighth place.
-Yes, eighth place.

1242
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:32,763
A stunning eighth place.

1243
00:50:32,829 --> 00:50:35,432
-What's eighth place? His ranking?
-Yes.

1244
00:50:35,499 --> 00:50:37,300
-Eighth place.
-Yet he's showing off like that?

1245
00:50:38,168 --> 00:50:40,404
Come on. Eighth place?

1246
00:50:40,470 --> 00:50:43,807
I thought he won the show.

1247
00:50:43,874 --> 00:50:45,842
The winner is right there, right?

1248
00:50:45,909 --> 00:50:48,345
-The winner.
-He's the winner.

1249
00:50:48,412 --> 00:50:51,715
But Chef Gyeong-jun
has been biding his time

1250
00:50:51,782 --> 00:50:53,850
after his defeat that day.

1251
00:50:53,917 --> 00:50:57,888
He wants to headbutt Hyun-suk and win.

1252
00:50:57,954 --> 00:51:00,657
-He'll headbutt him?
-Yes.

1253
00:51:00,724 --> 00:51:01,992
How scary.

1254
00:51:02,059 --> 00:51:04,761
It's also because this is his turf.

1255
00:51:04,828 --> 00:51:08,198
-I want to challenge him here and win.
-Yes.

1256
00:51:08,265 --> 00:51:10,934
He wants to win an away game.

1257
00:51:11,001 --> 00:51:13,737
Gyeong-jun is a new chef on the show,

1258
00:51:13,804 --> 00:51:15,505
-so you get a perk.
-He should get one.

1259
00:51:15,572 --> 00:51:17,374
There are three different perks.

1260
00:51:17,441 --> 00:51:19,509
-I'll use UNICHEF.
-UNICHEF.

1261
00:51:19,576 --> 00:51:21,211
UNICHEF for one minute.

1262
00:51:21,278 --> 00:51:23,613
-I'll ask Chef Nam-no here.
-Nam-no.

1263
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:25,682
Do you need just one? What about Fabri?

1264
00:51:25,749 --> 00:51:27,651
Then Chef Fabri too.

1265
00:51:27,717 --> 00:51:31,321
-Yes, two UNICHEF members.
-Two chefs, Nam-no and Fabri.

1266
00:51:32,155 --> 00:51:33,723
CHEF GYEONG-JUN: BUTTERBUR PICKLES,
FERMENTED CHILI PICKLES, BALSAMIC VINEGAR

1267
00:51:33,790 --> 00:51:35,325
SIRLOIN, TRUFFLE OIL, PAPRIKA, ORANGE,
PUMPKIN JUICE, SWEET PUMPKIN, AND MORE

1268
00:51:35,392 --> 00:51:37,794
Chef Gyeong-jun, what's your dish?

1269
00:51:37,861 --> 00:51:42,299
I'll make steak just for Hyun-sook.

1270
00:51:42,365 --> 00:51:44,101
What's it called?

1271
00:51:44,167 --> 00:51:45,869
-It's Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.
-Hyun-sook-teak.

1272
00:51:45,936 --> 00:51:47,637
-Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.
-Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.

1273
00:51:47,704 --> 00:51:49,473
-Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.
-Yes.

1274
00:51:49,539 --> 00:51:52,876
You had lots of side dishes,
including seasoned greens.

1275
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:55,178
I want to use the greens
and make Argentinian-style sauce

1276
00:51:55,245 --> 00:51:56,880
-called chimichurri.
-Chimichurri.

1277
00:51:56,947 --> 00:51:59,449
It's usually made with herbs like parsley,

1278
00:51:59,516 --> 00:52:01,885
but she had <i>chamnamul</i>, so I'll use that

1279
00:52:01,952 --> 00:52:05,288
<i>-and others like fermented chili pickles.</i>
<i>-And other greens.</i>

1280
00:52:05,889 --> 00:52:09,059
She said she wanted to have some steak,

1281
00:52:09,126 --> 00:52:11,194
-Yes.
-so I'll prepare tasty steak for her.

1282
00:52:11,261 --> 00:52:12,896
He's making steak.

1283
00:52:13,730 --> 00:52:15,265
CHEF HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS: HONEY, MANGO
FROZEN BOILED POTATO, RICE PAPER, CILANTRO

1284
00:52:15,332 --> 00:52:16,900
BRAISED TOFU IN SOY SAUCE, PEANUT BUTTER,
CHUCK FLAP TAIL, BALSAMIC VINEGAR, YOGURT

1285
00:52:16,967 --> 00:52:19,169
The dish I prepared is called

1286
00:52:19,236 --> 00:52:21,404
Paeng-tastic Steak.

1287
00:52:21,471 --> 00:52:24,374
-Not fantastic, but Paeng-tastic.
-What? Oh, Paeng-tastic.

1288
00:52:24,441 --> 00:52:27,410
-Paeng-tastic.
-It's Paeng-tastic Steak.

1289
00:52:27,477 --> 00:52:29,412
The spirit of my dishes are

1290
00:52:29,479 --> 00:52:32,616
familiar yet new.

1291
00:52:32,682 --> 00:52:34,985
I'll use braised tofu, rice paper,

1292
00:52:35,051 --> 00:52:37,020
and use
all the great ingredients she mentioned

1293
00:52:37,087 --> 00:52:41,525
and make steak that'll make her
feel like she's getting treated.

1294
00:52:41,591 --> 00:52:43,793
-I see.
-Gosh.

1295
00:52:43,860 --> 00:52:45,428
I'm looking forward to this. I'm nervous.

1296
00:52:45,495 --> 00:52:50,000
And now, they'll begin the round
titled beef over pork.

1297
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:52,602
Gosh, I'm getting teary.

1298
00:52:52,669 --> 00:52:54,237
-Yes.
-I'll watch it up there.

1299
00:52:54,304 --> 00:52:56,907
He's here to throw
a one-two punch at Hyun-suk

1300
00:52:56,973 --> 00:53:00,977
-and take out three of his teeth.
-Three teeth?

1301
00:53:01,044 --> 00:53:03,113
Don't say that.
He's old enough to be his dad.

1302
00:53:03,180 --> 00:53:05,015
He's nicknamed One Two Three.

1303
00:53:05,081 --> 00:53:06,783
One Two Three, Chef Bae Gyeong-jun.

1304
00:53:06,850 --> 00:53:08,185
He'll take the three teeth

1305
00:53:08,251 --> 00:53:11,988
and destroy every tooth
that Gyeong-jun has.

1306
00:53:13,156 --> 00:53:17,827
Choi Yang-rak of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Choi Hyun-suk.

1307
00:53:17,894 --> 00:53:19,095
It's okay.

1308
00:53:19,162 --> 00:53:22,232
Will Chef Gyeong-jun get his revenge?

1309
00:53:22,299 --> 00:53:26,469
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1310
00:53:28,772 --> 00:53:32,175
A RETURN MATCH OVER THEIR PRIDE!

1311
00:53:32,242 --> 00:53:33,376
HYUN-SUK BEGINS WITH THE MEAT

1312
00:53:33,443 --> 00:53:35,178
It's steak versus steak.

1313
00:53:35,245 --> 00:53:38,415
-Gosh, beef.
-Which cut are you using, Hyun-suk?

1314
00:53:38,481 --> 00:53:40,283
-Chuck flap tail.
-Chuck flap tail.

1315
00:53:40,350 --> 00:53:41,351
HOW'S GYEONG-JUN STARTING?

1316
00:53:41,418 --> 00:53:42,819
Whoa, hey.

1317
00:53:42,886 --> 00:53:44,454
HE BEGINS BY BROILING
VEGGIES OVER FIRE

1318
00:53:44,521 --> 00:53:46,923
-He's broiling green onion and paprika.
-Gosh.

1319
00:53:47,490 --> 00:53:50,193
-It's been a while since I've seen this.
-We do this often in Italy.

1320
00:53:50,660 --> 00:53:53,129
1. BROIL PAPRIKA, GREEN ONION
OVER FIRE AND BOIL PUMPKIN JUICE

1321
00:53:53,196 --> 00:53:55,999
Chef Gyeong-jun can use
the one-minute UNICHEF perk.

1322
00:53:56,066 --> 00:53:57,968
What are you grinding? Carrots?

1323
00:53:58,034 --> 00:53:59,569
Sweet pumpkin.

1324
00:54:00,103 --> 00:54:02,906
-Acorn squash.
-Acorn squash.

1325
00:54:02,973 --> 00:54:04,407
He's grinding acorn squash.

1326
00:54:04,474 --> 00:54:06,243
CAPTURING THE MOMENT

1327
00:54:06,309 --> 00:54:07,811
They're both grinding something.

1328
00:54:07,877 --> 00:54:10,180
They're both using the blender.

1329
00:54:12,182 --> 00:54:13,883
It doesn't work.

1330
00:54:14,451 --> 00:54:16,620
Will it work without any water?

1331
00:54:16,686 --> 00:54:19,656
-I think he's making purée.
-Purée?

1332
00:54:19,723 --> 00:54:21,558
I see. Yes.

1333
00:54:21,625 --> 00:54:22,926
It must be so soft.

1334
00:54:22,993 --> 00:54:26,162
-Chef Hyun-suk, did you mince the beef?
-The meat.

1335
00:54:28,031 --> 00:54:29,866
Hyun-suk, are those potatoes?

1336
00:54:29,933 --> 00:54:31,334
Yes, frozen potatoes.

1337
00:54:31,401 --> 00:54:33,270
Yes, I see.

1338
00:54:33,903 --> 00:54:36,506
HE GETS A ROUND COOKIE CUTTER

1339
00:54:38,875 --> 00:54:43,013
3. BUTTER A ROUND COOKIE CUTTER,
THEN PLACE BEEF INSIDE LIKE A BOWL

1340
00:54:43,079 --> 00:54:45,782
HUMMING

1341
00:54:46,283 --> 00:54:47,717
RELAXED

1342
00:54:48,218 --> 00:54:50,053
It's burnt. Is that okay?

1343
00:54:50,120 --> 00:54:51,254
Isn't it too burnt?

1344
00:54:51,321 --> 00:54:53,757
-It's too burnt. Look at the paprika.
-It's burnt.

1345
00:54:53,823 --> 00:54:55,158
He's doing it on purpose.

1346
00:54:55,225 --> 00:54:57,227
-He did it on purpose?
-He only uses the inside.

1347
00:54:57,294 --> 00:54:59,362
-I see. Whoa, Jung-hwan.
-He'll peel that off.

1348
00:54:59,429 --> 00:55:01,898
-Green onion is tasty when grilled.
-Yes.

1349
00:55:01,965 --> 00:55:04,601
-I hear it'll taste sweeter.
-Yes, it's the best.

1350
00:55:04,668 --> 00:55:06,970
-He's burning it on purpose?
-It's sweet even without sugar.

1351
00:55:08,238 --> 00:55:10,340
HE'S DONE
THAWING FROZEN POTATOES

1352
00:55:10,407 --> 00:55:12,842
Did he boil the potatoes already?

1353
00:55:12,909 --> 00:55:14,878
-Butter.
-He's adding butter to potatoes.

1354
00:55:14,944 --> 00:55:17,047
-Butter is best in Western cuisine.
-Right?

1355
00:55:17,113 --> 00:55:19,082
Hyun-suk is in a rush.

1356
00:55:19,149 --> 00:55:21,518
4. BLEND BOILED POTATO AND BUTTER
TO MAKE POTATO PURÉE

1357
00:55:22,886 --> 00:55:24,220
POTATO PURÉE

1358
00:55:24,287 --> 00:55:25,789
YOGURT

1359
00:55:25,855 --> 00:55:27,791
PEANUT BUTTER

1360
00:55:27,857 --> 00:55:30,593
Chef Hyun-suk,
what are you making that for?

1361
00:55:30,660 --> 00:55:32,462
I'll use it as stuffing.

1362
00:55:32,529 --> 00:55:33,797
What?

1363
00:55:33,863 --> 00:55:36,833
-What's a stuffing? Is it like filling?
-What goes inside like filling.

1364
00:55:41,471 --> 00:55:43,340
It doesn't grind well.

1365
00:55:43,406 --> 00:55:46,776
It won't.
I griddled the tofu, seasoned it,

1366
00:55:46,843 --> 00:55:47,844
then braised it again.

1367
00:55:47,911 --> 00:55:51,147
-I see. Is it tough?
-So it's going to be tough.

1368
00:55:51,214 --> 00:55:52,849
Hyun-suk is having trouble.

1369
00:55:53,783 --> 00:55:57,187
He completely burnt
the paprika and green onion.

1370
00:55:57,253 --> 00:55:59,356
It's like Calçotada.

1371
00:55:59,422 --> 00:56:01,091
She won't eat that, right?

1372
00:56:01,157 --> 00:56:04,527
-You eat the inside, right?
-He'll peel off the outside.

1373
00:56:04,594 --> 00:56:06,563
Right? That'll cause cancer.

1374
00:56:07,130 --> 00:56:08,598
OF COURSE

1375
00:56:08,665 --> 00:56:10,500
You have 12 minutes left.

1376
00:56:10,567 --> 00:56:12,602
-Already?
-Yes, you spent three minutes.

1377
00:56:12,669 --> 00:56:14,204
Gosh. Three minutes.

1378
00:56:14,270 --> 00:56:15,939
Time flies when we're focused.

1379
00:56:16,005 --> 00:56:18,875
Gosh, this is seriously insane.

1380
00:56:19,809 --> 00:56:22,946
GYEONG-JUN ROASTS FRUIT

1381
00:56:23,012 --> 00:56:24,347
He's roasting a tangerine.

1382
00:56:24,414 --> 00:56:27,016
-That's not a tangerine. It's an orange.
-It's an orange.

1383
00:56:27,650 --> 00:56:29,753
The fridge owner knows what it is.

1384
00:56:29,819 --> 00:56:31,254
It's really delicious.

1385
00:56:31,321 --> 00:56:33,823
-It tastes sweet.
-It tastes good when it's roasted.

1386
00:56:33,890 --> 00:56:35,959
-He's only roasting stuff.
-He only roasts everything.

1387
00:56:36,025 --> 00:56:37,827
-That's just his style.
-He should start cooking.

1388
00:56:37,894 --> 00:56:39,996
-He mostly smokes and roasts food.
-That's his cooking?

1389
00:56:40,063 --> 00:56:41,097
Is that his style?

1390
00:56:41,164 --> 00:56:43,299
He burns the food
like he's playing with fire.

1391
00:56:43,366 --> 00:56:45,802
-Playing with fire?
-Gyeong-jun only plays with fire.

1392
00:56:45,869 --> 00:56:47,804
He burnt the inside.

1393
00:56:47,871 --> 00:56:49,305
Is the orange okay?

1394
00:56:49,873 --> 00:56:51,574
THE ORANGE IS FULLY BURNT

1395
00:56:51,641 --> 00:56:54,811
If he puts it in a bowl and covers it,

1396
00:56:54,878 --> 00:56:58,214
the moisture will
make it easier to peel it off.

1397
00:56:58,281 --> 00:57:00,016
He's doing it to peel it off?

1398
00:57:00,083 --> 00:57:01,217
I see.

1399
00:57:01,284 --> 00:57:04,554
-Let me know when you need help.
-Okay.

1400
00:57:05,355 --> 00:57:08,858
HE FINISHES MAKING
THE POTATO AND TOFU STUFFING

1401
00:57:10,226 --> 00:57:12,262
What's Chef Hyun-suk doing?

1402
00:57:12,328 --> 00:57:16,065
-He's stuffing the minced beef.
-I see.

1403
00:57:16,132 --> 00:57:19,402
It's like hamburger steak.

1404
00:57:19,469 --> 00:57:21,337
-I see.
-I see.

1405
00:57:21,404 --> 00:57:23,373
He'll stuff it with stuffing like cheese.

1406
00:57:23,440 --> 00:57:27,177
7. GRILL CHUCK FLAP TAIL STEAK
IN A PAN OILED WITH OLIVE OIL

1407
00:57:27,243 --> 00:57:30,079
He's grilling the meat in that shape.

1408
00:57:30,146 --> 00:57:33,316
-It's hamburger steak.
-That's the shape of his steak.

1409
00:57:33,383 --> 00:57:34,651
Ten minutes.

1410
00:57:34,717 --> 00:57:36,419
-Hey, ten minutes.
-Ten minutes.

1411
00:57:37,020 --> 00:57:38,354
FUMBLING AROUND

1412
00:57:38,421 --> 00:57:40,123
