01:07:09,625 --> 01:07:13,095
He's putting sauce on his steak.
I hope he's happy with this one.

1656
01:07:13,162 --> 01:07:16,032
Keep it up, Gyeong-jun!

1657
01:07:17,299 --> 01:07:19,235
You can do it, Gyeong-jun!

1658
01:07:19,301 --> 01:07:20,636
Are you done?

1659
01:07:20,703 --> 01:07:22,905
You can do it, Gyeong-jun!

1660
01:07:22,972 --> 01:07:24,740
Are you done?

1661
01:07:24,807 --> 01:07:26,942
JUST AMAZED

1662
01:07:27,510 --> 01:07:29,045
-Thirty seconds!
-Thirty seconds!

1663
01:07:29,111 --> 01:07:30,713
Gyeong-jun, 30 seconds!

1664
01:07:30,780 --> 01:07:33,282
It's okay. It's now 25 seconds.

1665
01:07:33,349 --> 01:07:36,252
When will you put this in?
You're out of time.

1666
01:07:36,318 --> 01:07:37,353
You have to hurry.

1667
01:07:37,420 --> 01:07:39,188
-Fifteen.
-Fifteen seconds!

1668
01:07:39,255 --> 01:07:40,856
Fifteen seconds!

1669
01:07:40,923 --> 01:07:42,625
-Ten seconds.
-Ten seconds.

1670
01:07:42,691 --> 01:07:44,727
-Ten. Nine.
-He's done.

1671
01:07:44,794 --> 01:07:46,595
-Eight. Seven.
-Eight. Seven.

1672
01:07:46,662 --> 01:07:48,264
-I got it.
-Six. Five.

1673
01:07:48,330 --> 01:07:51,400
-You still have time.
-Four. Three.

1674
01:07:51,467 --> 01:07:53,803
-Ring the bell! He rang the bell.
-Two. One.

1675
01:07:53,869 --> 01:07:56,138
GYEONG-JUN FINISHES
PAENG HYUN-SOOK-TEAK

1676
01:07:56,205 --> 01:07:57,206
That's so cool.

1677
01:07:57,273 --> 01:07:58,808
They're both done.

1678
01:07:58,874 --> 01:07:59,942
Chef Gyeong-jun.

1679
01:08:01,210 --> 01:08:02,945
I forgot to top it with green onion.

1680
01:08:03,012 --> 01:08:04,580
What? Just let him put that on.

1681
01:08:04,647 --> 01:08:06,949
-Let him use this.
-Let me top it with green onion.

1682
01:08:07,016 --> 01:08:09,351
He can't make changes when the time is up,

1683
01:08:09,418 --> 01:08:10,786
but let him use this.

1684
01:08:12,388 --> 01:08:13,489
-Top it.
-Do it.

1685
01:08:13,556 --> 01:08:14,557
Go.

1686
01:08:14,623 --> 01:08:16,792
It was the blender.

1687
01:08:16,859 --> 01:08:20,796
-It took up a lot of time.
-It's his fault for not checking,

1688
01:08:20,863 --> 01:08:22,064
but I'll let him do it.

1689
01:08:22,131 --> 01:08:25,434
-My gosh.
-Why can't he stay quiet?

1690
01:08:25,501 --> 01:08:29,638
He had it made already,
so we'll let him use it.

1691
01:08:31,740 --> 01:08:35,945
And now, the beef dishes
for Hyun-sook are both ready.

1692
01:08:36,011 --> 01:08:37,780
-Thank you.
-Yes.

1693
01:08:37,847 --> 01:08:41,750
Hyun-sook said
she wanted to see a pretty dish.

1694
01:08:41,817 --> 01:08:43,486
-That's important.
-Aren't they so pretty?

1695
01:08:44,253 --> 01:08:47,623
What looks good will taste good too.
This was what I wanted.

1696
01:08:47,690 --> 01:08:49,758
I wanted to live this kind of life.

1697
01:08:50,326 --> 01:08:51,727
CHUCKLE

1698
01:08:51,794 --> 01:08:56,098
You can begin
with Chef Hyun-suk's Paeng-tastic Steak.

1699
01:08:57,199 --> 01:09:00,536
RICE PAPER STEAK
WITH MINCED CHUCK TAIL FLAP

1700
01:09:01,704 --> 01:09:05,207
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
PAENG-TASTIC STEAK

1701
01:09:05,274 --> 01:09:07,443
The potato was puréed with mango.

1702
01:09:07,510 --> 01:09:08,911
Yes, you threw in mango.

1703
01:09:08,978 --> 01:09:11,547
-Top the meat with the purée,
-Right? It's so new.

1704
01:09:11,614 --> 01:09:13,716
cut out a bite,
and eat everything together.

1705
01:09:13,782 --> 01:09:15,918
You'll taste that soft chuck flap tail.

1706
01:09:15,985 --> 01:09:19,154
It would've been so nice
if my life was as smooth as this.

1707
01:09:19,221 --> 01:09:20,789
She dreamed of living this life.

1708
01:09:20,856 --> 01:09:22,391
-May I eat it?
-Go ahead.

1709
01:09:22,458 --> 01:09:25,094
This is… I don't want to destroy this art.

1710
01:09:25,161 --> 01:09:26,896
Let me take a bite from the tip.

1711
01:09:26,962 --> 01:09:28,697
-No, tear it down.
-Tear it down.

1712
01:09:28,764 --> 01:09:31,333
-That's the fun.
-But it's such a shame.

1713
01:09:31,400 --> 01:09:33,536
-That's the fun?
-Is it?

1714
01:09:33,602 --> 01:09:36,038
-The mango.
-She puts some sauce on it.

1715
01:09:36,105 --> 01:09:37,506
Paeng-tastic Steak.

1716
01:09:37,573 --> 01:09:40,409
-I have to eat it with some class.
-Use a spoon.

1717
01:09:40,476 --> 01:09:42,778
How can I use a spoon
when I eat a Western dish?

1718
01:09:42,845 --> 01:09:45,080
I can't do that.

1719
01:09:45,147 --> 01:09:46,849
-Can you eat it already?
-Use a spoon.

1720
01:09:47,883 --> 01:09:49,785
I'm dying to know.

1721
01:09:49,852 --> 01:09:51,287
-We don't want it to get cold.
-No.

1722
01:09:51,353 --> 01:09:53,656
She got everything ready.

1723
01:09:53,722 --> 01:09:54,723
Take a big bite.

1724
01:09:55,424 --> 01:09:56,425
A BIG BITE

1725
01:09:56,492 --> 01:09:59,195
That's Paeng-tastic Steak.

1726
01:09:59,261 --> 01:10:00,329
What is it, Hyun-sook?

1727
01:10:01,063 --> 01:10:02,598
My gosh.

1728
01:10:02,665 --> 01:10:04,400
Let me try another bite.

1729
01:10:04,466 --> 01:10:06,435
-Some sauce.
-The sauce.

1730
01:10:08,103 --> 01:10:10,472
Yes, so what's it like?

1731
01:10:11,440 --> 01:10:13,209
I'm dying to find out.

1732
01:10:14,243 --> 01:10:17,179
-I need to try it again--
-No! Will you stop eating that?

1733
01:10:17,246 --> 01:10:19,215
You have to tell us what it's like.

1734
01:10:19,281 --> 01:10:20,716
How long do we have to wait?

1735
01:10:20,783 --> 01:10:24,420
-First, the meat is tender.
-It was cooked well.

1736
01:10:24,486 --> 01:10:26,655
It's made with chuck flap tail,
so it's very tender.

1737
01:10:26,722 --> 01:10:28,791
Everything was cooked perfectly.

1738
01:10:28,857 --> 01:10:32,161
Also, he already had it destroyed.

1739
01:10:32,228 --> 01:10:34,396
Destroyed? Come on.

1740
01:10:34,463 --> 01:10:38,434
And toward the end,
you can taste that fatty bit.

1741
01:10:38,500 --> 01:10:39,868
That savory fat flavor.

1742
01:10:39,935 --> 01:10:41,437
-The creamy taste.
-The meat taste.

1743
01:10:41,503 --> 01:10:43,305
The meat flavor is fantastic.

1744
01:10:43,372 --> 01:10:44,740
Was the meat a bit burnt?

1745
01:10:44,807 --> 01:10:46,675
No, not at all.

1746
01:10:46,742 --> 01:10:49,311
It can get a bit greasy,

1747
01:10:49,378 --> 01:10:52,114
but this sauce made with mango

1748
01:10:52,181 --> 01:10:55,017
-adds that sour, refreshing taste.
-I see.

1749
01:10:55,084 --> 01:10:56,252
I wonder what the purée is like.

1750
01:10:56,318 --> 01:11:00,189
So when the steak gets too greasy,
the sauce comes in and plays a part.

1751
01:11:00,256 --> 01:11:02,524
It's like hitting and receiving.

1752
01:11:02,591 --> 01:11:04,059
-That's great.
-It's exquisite.

1753
01:11:04,126 --> 01:11:06,328
This is an unprecedented taste.

1754
01:11:06,395 --> 01:11:08,564
<i>-He put something in there, right?</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

1755
01:11:08,631 --> 01:11:13,302
<i>I stuffed it with peanut butter, yogurt,</i>
<i>braised tofu, and potato.</i>

1756
01:11:13,369 --> 01:11:15,304
It's an interesting combination.

1757
01:11:15,371 --> 01:11:19,675
It's made with tofu and peanuts,
which are both protein.

1758
01:11:19,742 --> 01:11:22,077
You brought out the nutty flavor
two, no, even three times more.

1759
01:11:22,144 --> 01:11:24,647
-It's excellent.
-He's amazing.

1760
01:11:24,713 --> 01:11:27,149
-Let your husband have a bite.
-Yang-rak.

1761
01:11:27,216 --> 01:11:28,851
Eat just half of it. Don't finish it.

1762
01:11:29,652 --> 01:11:31,053
YANG-RAK TAKES A BITE TOO

1763
01:11:31,120 --> 01:11:32,988
Yang-rak.

1764
01:11:33,055 --> 01:11:35,424
So? What's it like?

1765
01:11:35,491 --> 01:11:37,960
-They cooked with pork before, right?
-Yes.

1766
01:11:38,027 --> 01:11:40,863
This is what I don't like about beef.

1767
01:11:40,929 --> 01:11:43,198
OH, MY

1768
01:11:43,265 --> 01:11:46,535
Come on. It's so delicious.

1769
01:11:46,602 --> 01:11:48,837
It's just delicious.

1770
01:11:48,904 --> 01:11:50,906
It's just subtle.

1771
01:11:50,973 --> 01:11:53,609
-But pork is more passionate.
-Yes, it's passionate.

1772
01:11:53,676 --> 01:11:57,279
I prefer pork over beef.

1773
01:11:57,346 --> 01:12:01,750
I like subtle taste,
whereas Yang-rak likes something strong.

1774
01:12:03,252 --> 01:12:04,987
Take a big bite.

1775
01:12:05,054 --> 01:12:08,590
Look how the steak is falling apart.
It doesn't look so great.

1776
01:12:08,657 --> 01:12:10,559
If you're jealous, just say so.

1777
01:12:10,626 --> 01:12:11,627
-My gosh.
-I'm jealous.

1778
01:12:11,694 --> 01:12:13,362
No, you can't have it.

1779
01:12:13,429 --> 01:12:15,097
She's enjoying it in a classy way.

1780
01:12:15,164 --> 01:12:17,499
What's it like when you mixed it up?

1781
01:12:17,566 --> 01:12:19,234
Everything comes together.

1782
01:12:19,301 --> 01:12:21,370
-It all came together.
-Together?

1783
01:12:21,437 --> 01:12:23,605
-It all works well?
-It goes well together.

1784
01:12:23,672 --> 01:12:24,673
My gosh.

1785
01:12:24,740 --> 01:12:29,578
This is one of the steaks
I enjoyed the most in my life.

1786
01:12:29,645 --> 01:12:32,281
-It's like hamburger steak.
-Hamburger steak.

1787
01:12:32,348 --> 01:12:35,184
It's really addictive.
You keep craving it.

1788
01:12:35,250 --> 01:12:36,985
-It makes you keep wanting more.
-Yes.

1789
01:12:37,052 --> 01:12:39,455
And he topped it off with cilantro,

1790
01:12:39,521 --> 01:12:40,756
and it's…

1791
01:12:40,823 --> 01:12:44,993
-That's why he's an expert.
-Yes, it's really good.

1792
01:12:45,060 --> 01:12:47,763
<i>And next, Chef Gyeong-jun's dish.</i>

1793
01:12:47,830 --> 01:12:49,798
<i>Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.</i>

1794
01:12:49,865 --> 01:12:52,634
CHIMICHURRI SAUCE MADE
WITH HYUN-SOOK'S SIDE DISHES

1795
01:12:53,836 --> 01:12:57,473
CHEF BAE GYEONG-JUN'S
PAENG HYUN-SOOK-TEAK

1796
01:12:57,539 --> 01:13:00,175
-This looks more like what you like.
-I'm about to cry.

1797
01:13:00,242 --> 01:13:02,444
-It's pretty.
-It looks pretty too.

1798
01:13:02,511 --> 01:13:05,381
Oh, my. May I eat this piece of art?

1799
01:13:05,447 --> 01:13:07,149
Yes, so please take a bite.

1800
01:13:07,216 --> 01:13:08,951
She dips it in the sauce.

1801
01:13:09,017 --> 01:13:12,054
Chef Gyeong-jun
worked very hard on the sauce.

1802
01:13:12,921 --> 01:13:13,956
What's it like?

1803
01:13:14,022 --> 01:13:15,224
What's it like?

1804
01:13:15,290 --> 01:13:16,725
WHAT'S IT LIKE?

1805
01:13:16,792 --> 01:13:20,362
At first, the sauce's strong flavor
hits me first.

1806
01:13:20,429 --> 01:13:21,730
After that,

1807
01:13:21,797 --> 01:13:24,833
the tenderness of the meat,
the sirloin gets me.

1808
01:13:24,900 --> 01:13:26,201
-Have you ever had sirloin?
-Of course.

1809
01:13:26,268 --> 01:13:28,137
That sirloin flavor. That's it.

1810
01:13:28,203 --> 01:13:30,038
-"Have you ever had sirloin?"
-I've had it.

1811
01:13:30,105 --> 01:13:31,540
And the green onion.

1812
01:13:31,607 --> 01:13:33,642
-Was it cooked well?
-It was nearly burnt.

1813
01:13:33,709 --> 01:13:36,278
-He broiled it before.
-He broiled it. Right?

1814
01:13:36,345 --> 01:13:39,848
-I can taste the smoky flavor.
-That was why.

1815
01:13:39,915 --> 01:13:42,017
UNICHEF helped him out.

1816
01:13:42,084 --> 01:13:45,621
-It even has a tender texture.
-Well done.

1817
01:13:45,687 --> 01:13:47,523
I can smell perilla leaf too.

1818
01:13:48,357 --> 01:13:51,527
Yang-rak wants to smell it.

1819
01:13:51,593 --> 01:13:52,761
My gosh.

1820
01:13:52,828 --> 01:13:54,596
I can smell green onion and meat.

1821
01:13:54,663 --> 01:13:59,101
-The smoky flavor adds more class.
-Yang-rak got lucky with his wife.

1822
01:13:59,168 --> 01:14:02,805
What will Yang-rak think of this?
He doesn't enjoy beef too much.

1823
01:14:02,871 --> 01:14:03,872
He'll say the same thing.

1824
01:14:03,939 --> 01:14:05,908
-My gosh.
-Hey, Yang-rak.

1825
01:14:05,974 --> 01:14:07,409
-What is it?
-What?

1826
01:14:07,476 --> 01:14:09,211
It's worse than pork, right?

1827
01:14:09,278 --> 01:14:11,113
-No.
-He's different from before.

1828
01:14:11,180 --> 01:14:12,848
His eyes got bigger.

1829
01:14:12,915 --> 01:14:15,250
This is why people like beef.

1830
01:14:15,851 --> 01:14:19,721
-He finally gets why people like beef.
-That was a significant remark.

1831
01:14:19,788 --> 01:14:21,490
"This is why people like beef."

1832
01:14:21,557 --> 01:14:23,192
-Do you like it?
-The texture

1833
01:14:23,258 --> 01:14:25,427
made me feel like
I was eating something hearty.

1834
01:14:25,494 --> 01:14:28,197
<i>And it was delicious</i>
<i>when I had it with green onion.</i>

1835
01:14:28,263 --> 01:14:29,665
-Gosh.
-It tastes luxurious.

1836
01:14:29,731 --> 01:14:31,500
It captured me

1837
01:14:31,567 --> 01:14:32,568
with one bite.

1838
01:14:32,634 --> 01:14:34,436
That's the best compliment.

1839
01:14:34,503 --> 01:14:35,838
HIS STEAK WAS RECEIVED WELL
BY THE PORK LOVER

1840
01:14:35,904 --> 01:14:37,272
Why don't we all try it together?

1841
01:14:37,339 --> 01:14:41,376
Let's try Chef Hyun-suk's dish first.

1842
01:14:41,443 --> 01:14:42,744
Paeng-tastic Steak.

1843
01:14:42,811 --> 01:14:44,413
Hey, it's good.

1844
01:14:44,480 --> 01:14:46,849
-Man, it smells so good.
-The peanut butter works very well.

1845
01:14:47,382 --> 01:14:48,383
Isn't it good?

1846
01:14:48,450 --> 01:14:49,451
SLURPS

1847
01:14:50,018 --> 01:14:52,321
-It's really good.
-It's like tender Eonyang-style bulgogi.

1848
01:14:52,387 --> 01:14:53,422
Yes.

1849
01:14:53,489 --> 01:14:56,592
-That's the texture, but it's classier.
-Yes.

1850
01:14:56,658 --> 01:14:58,293
That's something you grill over fire.

1851
01:14:58,360 --> 01:15:01,396
You can't eat much of chuck flap tail
because it's too greasy.

1852
01:15:01,463 --> 01:15:03,499
-Yes, it's very fatty.
-It is.

1853
01:15:03,565 --> 01:15:04,800
But he minced it.

1854
01:15:04,867 --> 01:15:09,137
So even when I take a small bite,
it smells like I had a hearty portion.

1855
01:15:09,204 --> 01:15:10,772
-Yes, that's right.
-I think

1856
01:15:10,839 --> 01:15:14,810
<i>it'll be an excellent bar snack,</i>
<i>a great pair with wine.</i>

1857
01:15:14,877 --> 01:15:18,514
He added sweetness with mango, not sugar.

1858
01:15:18,580 --> 01:15:23,085
-So it felt really pure.
-The naturally sweet taste.

1859
01:15:23,151 --> 01:15:25,954
-The balance was excellent.
-Excellent balance.

1860
01:15:26,021 --> 01:15:27,656
THANK YOU

1861
01:15:27,723 --> 01:15:31,059
And now, Chef Gyeong-jun's
Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.

1862
01:15:31,126 --> 01:15:33,161
I'll eat it all at once.

1863
01:15:34,196 --> 01:15:35,864
-It's good.
-This is good.

1864
01:15:35,931 --> 01:15:39,001
The smell of paprika
in the sauce over here is insane.

1865
01:15:39,067 --> 01:15:40,969
It smells like South America.

1866
01:15:41,036 --> 01:15:42,437
It smells South American.

1867
01:15:42,504 --> 01:15:45,274
When he blended raw veggies,

1868
01:15:45,340 --> 01:15:47,442
-I was worried it'd smell grassy.
-Yes.

1869
01:15:47,509 --> 01:15:50,746
But it added savory flavor
thanks to the pickled side dishes.

1870
01:15:50,812 --> 01:15:53,215
<i>The balance of the meat is on point.</i>

1871
01:15:53,282 --> 01:15:55,117
<i>That was really special.</i>

1872
01:15:55,183 --> 01:15:58,387
-Have you tried mixing these before?
-How did you know?

1873
01:15:58,453 --> 01:15:59,922
I've made chimichurri sauce before,

1874
01:15:59,988 --> 01:16:02,524
but never with pickled vegetables.

1875
01:16:02,591 --> 01:16:05,027
It was because her pickles were that good.

1876
01:16:05,093 --> 01:16:07,162
I saw everything he put in,

1877
01:16:07,229 --> 01:16:09,364
and he added one clove of pickled garlic.

1878
01:16:09,431 --> 01:16:10,832
-That spicy flavor
-The final touch.

1879
01:16:10,899 --> 01:16:14,770
which keeps popping up is
that single clove of garlic.

1880
01:16:14,836 --> 01:16:17,673
-That was exquisite.
-He's very detailed.

1881
01:16:17,739 --> 01:16:19,775
-He's very delicate.
-You could say it's scientific.

1882
01:16:19,841 --> 01:16:21,410
It's now your turn to choose.

1883
01:16:21,476 --> 01:16:23,445
This must be hard. This one was hard.

1884
01:16:23,512 --> 01:16:26,114
I just want to go home
instead of choosing one.

1885
01:16:26,181 --> 01:16:28,150
You can go after you choose.

1886
01:16:28,650 --> 01:16:30,519
You must pick one.

1887
01:16:30,586 --> 01:16:34,456
<i>Press one for Chef Gyeong-jun's</i>
<i>Paeng Hyun-sook-teak.</i>

1888
01:16:34,523 --> 01:16:37,960
<i>Press two for Chef Hyun-suk's</i>
<i>Paeng-tastic Steak.</i>

1889
01:16:38,026 --> 01:16:39,528
Please make your decision

1890
01:16:39,595 --> 01:16:41,830
and press the button.

1891
01:16:41,897 --> 01:16:43,699
This one is really hard.

1892
01:16:43,765 --> 01:16:45,567
-I made my choice.
-She chose one.

1893
01:16:45,634 --> 01:16:49,004
Let's find out which one she chose.

1894
01:16:49,071 --> 01:16:50,739
Who became the winner?

1895
01:16:50,806 --> 01:16:52,007
Let's find out the result.

1896
01:16:52,074 --> 01:16:54,009
Beef over pork.

1897
01:16:54,076 --> 01:16:55,644
She wanted beef dishes.

1898
01:16:55,711 --> 01:16:59,481
Will Hyun-suk win
and seize the victory again?

1899
01:16:59,548 --> 01:17:03,585
Or will Gyeong-jun take Hyun-suk down

1900
01:17:03,652 --> 01:17:05,921
and take the star?

1901
01:17:05,988 --> 01:17:08,590
Who did Hyun-sook choose?

1902
01:17:09,324 --> 01:17:11,994
Many eyes are on this match!

1903
01:17:12,060 --> 01:17:13,061
Who's the winner?

1904
01:17:13,829 --> 01:17:15,063
Who is it?

1905
01:17:15,931 --> 01:17:17,733
CHEF BAE GYEONG-JUN'S
PAENG HYUN-SOOK-TEAK WINS

1906
01:17:17,799 --> 01:17:18,900
Bae Gyeong-jun!

1907
01:17:19,468 --> 01:17:20,469
Don't get me wrong.

1908
01:17:20,535 --> 01:17:23,405
Your dish was delicious. I'm so sorry.

1909
01:17:23,472 --> 01:17:24,840
-Gyeong-jun wins.
-It was good.

1910
01:17:26,008 --> 01:17:28,543
Hyun-sook chose Gyeong-jun.

1911
01:17:28,610 --> 01:17:34,082
Both chefs did a wonderful job,
and the dishes were all delicious.

1912
01:17:34,149 --> 01:17:39,287
But Chef Hyun-suk is
already on the top of his game.

1913
01:17:39,354 --> 01:17:42,524
However, Chef Gyeong-jun

1914
01:17:42,591 --> 01:17:44,593
-felt like my son.
-I see.

1915
01:17:44,660 --> 01:17:47,195
-His future…
-What kind of decision is that?

1916
01:17:47,262 --> 01:17:50,666
-You should've decided with their food.
-Everything was good.

1917
01:17:50,732 --> 01:17:52,334
Actually,

1918
01:17:52,401 --> 01:17:55,537
I personally prefer sirloin
over chuck flap tail.

1919
01:17:55,604 --> 01:17:58,373
-It was the cut.
-He chose the wrong cut.

1920
01:17:58,440 --> 01:18:00,175
-The wrong cut.
-It was the wrong cut.

1921
01:18:00,242 --> 01:18:01,877
Why did you use the chuck flap tail?

1922
01:18:01,943 --> 01:18:03,745
-That's tasty too, but…
-It was her preference.

1923
01:18:03,812 --> 01:18:05,547
-I'm sorry.
-It's all right.

1924
01:18:05,614 --> 01:18:07,482
-It was delicious.
-My gosh.

1925
01:18:07,549 --> 01:18:11,553
Gyeong-jun takes down Hyun-suk
as soon as he debuts!

1926
01:18:12,254 --> 01:18:13,488
I'm jealous.

1927
01:18:13,555 --> 01:18:15,524
-Congratulations.
-He did it.

1928
01:18:16,091 --> 01:18:17,726
Chef Gyeong-jun wins!

1929
01:18:18,460 --> 01:18:19,761
He's my role model.

1930
01:18:19,828 --> 01:18:20,996
The early bird only gets tired.

1931
01:18:21,063 --> 01:18:22,564
-Good!
-Good!

1932
01:18:22,631 --> 01:18:25,434
Why are you changing
my greatest quotes into Myung-soo's?

1933
01:18:25,500 --> 01:18:27,569
People like him become a success.

1934
01:18:27,636 --> 01:18:30,338
I'm not scared of anything.
If it's bad, I'll say it's bad.

1935
01:18:30,405 --> 01:18:31,707
He'll get slapped at this rate.

1936
01:18:31,773 --> 01:18:32,874
Slap me, then.

1937
01:18:32,941 --> 01:18:35,577
Why are you fighting on this good day?
Stop bickering.

1938
01:18:36,144 --> 01:18:39,481
<i>I'll show you the revenge</i>
<i>of the original Italian.</i>

1939
01:18:39,548 --> 01:18:40,615
<i>I'm confident.</i>

1940
01:18:40,682 --> 01:18:41,683
<i>I'm a bit nervous.</i>

1941
01:18:41,750 --> 01:18:44,820
<i>He said he came ready to get revenge,</i>
<i>but I didn't plan on losing, either.</i>

1942
01:18:46,321 --> 01:18:49,324
-Hey, gochujang! It's flower-shaped.
-That's cool.

1943
01:18:49,391 --> 01:18:51,193
-This episode is legendary.
-That's Italian.

1944
01:18:51,259 --> 01:18:52,427
It's Italian!

1945
01:18:52,494 --> 01:18:53,695
That was it!

1946
01:18:53,762 --> 01:18:54,930
The return match between the crazy guys.

1947
01:18:54,996 --> 01:18:56,398
It's like their lives depend on it.

1948
01:18:56,465 --> 01:18:57,632
This is so gross.

1949
01:18:57,699 --> 01:18:58,834
It's so hot!

1950
01:18:58,900 --> 01:19:00,435
It looks like leftovers.

1951
01:19:00,502 --> 01:19:01,970
Just get out of here!

1952
01:19:02,037 --> 01:19:03,438
He has a cold-hearted evaluation.

1953
01:19:04,306 --> 01:19:06,341
He just slammed his fork on the table.

1954
01:19:06,408 --> 01:19:08,176
<i>-What does it mean?</i>
<i>-What is it?</i>

1955
01:19:08,243 --> 01:19:10,445
Don't give me your leftovers!

1956
01:19:10,512 --> 01:19:12,013
Do you think I'm a joke?

1957
01:19:21,289 --> 01:19:26,294
Subtitle translation by: Eunsook Youn
